The lead designer of the rifle is Pyotr Serdyukov. The AS Val and VSS proved to be very effective and remain in service with elements of the Russian army and special forces and Moscows intelligence and security forces.

A large, genetically-engineered mite. Thick chitin plates and an anaerobic metabolism allow it to survive in space. Originally designed as part of an organic asteroid-mining system, the project was abandoned when the hives proved too difficult to control. Like other eusocial arthropods, it cannot reproduce individually.

The Steyr AUG (Armee-Universal-Gewehr"universal army rifle") is an Austrian 5.5645mm NATO bullpup assault rifle, designed in the 1960s by Steyr-Daimler-Puch and now manufactured by Steyr Mannlicher GmbH & Co KG.  It was adopted by the Austrian Army as the StG 77 (Sturmgewehr 77) in 1978, where it replaced the 7.6251mm NATO StG 58 automatic rifle (a licence-built FN FAL). In production since 1978, it is the standard small arm of the Austrian Bundesheer and various national police units. Its variants have also been adopted by the armed forces of dozens of countries.

The Auger Mark II is an upgraded version of the standard Auger Rifle, allows users to aim at targets and fire through walls. The Auger Mark II comes with a transparent visor which reveals the thermal signature of any enemies through walls, making the Mark II perfect for neutralizing enemies without having to guess where they are as with the previous Auger.   The transient radiation charges of the Auger Mk II has improved firepower, along with the better accuracy that the rifle now has.

A payload of avian genetic material. Can be used at the genomorpher to create a growth cell of a hybrid animal. This tier 1 genome can be used as either a primary or secondary genome.  <color=#E5E54C>Gameplay effect:</color> All primary avian hybrids lay eggs. Combat avian hybrids get increased movement speed.  <color=#E5E54C>Extraction:</color> Can be extracted via the genome extractor table or any genome excavator from:

Directly injects avian genes in an humanoid. This genetrainer gives the birdlike curiosity health state, increasing global learning speed.  Genetrainers are implants that do not take the place of any given organ. Only one can be "installed" at a time. Using a second genetrainer will have no effect. Bear in mind that a genetrainer modifies the genes of the human subject, and only death will get rid of its effects.

Sure the little blighter is more stubborn than its progenitor, but not having to gather the eggs so often and a bigger fried egg makes all the difference.  A perfect avian animal, paragon of all similar animals with no needless junk genetic data. Besides the various improvements to the baseline animals abilities, this paragon possesses inherent wildness not present in domesticated chickens but is more likely to stay put.

Fertilized avian paragon egg. It can be eaten raw, but it's much, much better cooked. These eggs are pure, pristine, perfect examples of chicken eggs. Immaculate eggness. If all goes well, it should hatch into an avian paragon.
Unfertilized avian paragon egg. It can be eaten raw, but it's much, much better cooked. These eggs are pure, pristine, perfect examples of chicken eggs. Immaculate eggness.
Polenta that has been baked into a bread.
fast growing grass used for construction.
This special pot is suitable for planting bamboo bonsai trees, which can improve the mood of people nearby and satisfy ideoligious requirements.
A yellow fruit that grows on trees.
A pack of bandages made from cloth. Less potent than medical kits.
Cereal grain used for livestock feed, cooked for food, and used for beer making.
A drink made from brewed barley.   Drink Effects: Blood Filtration.

A baseball bat is a smooth wooden or metal club used in the sport of baseball to hit the ball after it is thrown by the pitcher. By regulation it may be no more than 2.75 inches (7.0 cm) in diameter at the thickest part and no more than 42 inches (1.067 m) in length. Although historically bats approaching 3 pounds (1.4 kg) were swung, modern bats of 33 ounces (0.94 kg) are more common, topping out at 34 ounces (0.96 kg) to 36 ounces (1.0 kg)

A baseball bat is a smooth wooden or metal club used in the sport of baseball to hit the ball after it is thrown by the pitcher. By regulation it may be no more than 2.75 inches (7.0 cm) in diameter at the thickest part and no more than 42 inches (1.067 m) in length. Although historically bats approaching 3 pounds (1.4 kg) were swung, modern bats of 33 ounces (0.94 kg) are more common, topping out at 34 ounces (0.96 kg) to 36 ounces (1.0 kg)  This version of baseball bat is of the Cold Steel Brooklyn Smasher line.
A makeshift hologram emitter connected to a gaming PC. Capable of only simple simulations. Users will slowly gain skill points depending on the chosen sim.

items.armor: Armor - Sharp: 70%, Armor - Blunt: 35%, Armor - Heat: 35%
items.description: A charming combination of a light plasteel exo-skeleton and devilstrand-reinforced uniform with a sassy skirt. Female combat androids favor this style, which accentuates combat methodology: speed and overwhelming aggression.

A race of rudimentary humanlike warrior robots.  Usually found guarding the homes of the wealthy and offices of mega corporations. They show no mercy upon targets who fail to identify themselves. Are traditionally armed with miniguns and core launchers.
A kit containing a disassembled Battle droid with all the tools required to assemble it.

items.armor: Armor - Sharp: 20%, Armor - Blunt: 20%, Armor - Heat: 10%
items.description: A traditional looking maid hat with a military theme. Comes with a headset for communicating with allies.
Common bean cooked up in many ways.

An unusual concoction of traits that was favoured by a particular client who was obsessed on making things explode. Earned the nickname Boom-Boom as they would often make requests along the lines of two more booms, wasnt paying attention.  An ursine hybrid with recessive boomalope genes. Lacking intelligence compared to a bear while also missing out on some strength and confidence in hunting. However, they can be commanded to detonate a limited amount of fuel sacks for increased combat versatility in exchange for hurting themselves intentionally.  <color=#E5E54C>Gameplay effect:</color> All primary bear hybrids have stun attacks. The "Detonate chemfuel" ability can be used to cause a powerful "Bomb" damage type explosion surrounding the hybrid. Bear in mind (pun intended) that this will damage the hybrid too!

These are small, pink berries known as bearberries. While raw bearberries possess an acidic and bland taste, after cooking a natural sweetness comes through and the results can be much more palatable.

Massive, fluffy murder babies is just one of the many cute nicknames made for this animal, their only downside being that theyre unable to purr. Because theyre so large, they often end up knocking over the people theyre trying to show affection to before laying on top of them for warmth.  An ursine hybrid with recessive feline genes. Retaining their intelligence and being faster and more fierce in combat, they are adorable killing machines that love to nuzzle. They prefer easier prey and can be slaughtered for a valuable pelt, you monster.  <color=#E5E54C>Gameplay effect:</color> All primary bear hybrids have stun attacks. Like all cat hybrids, they have an improved melee dodge ability and a short nuzzle period. The pelt can be sold or used in the art workbench to create rugs.
This enormous bear pelt is probably valuable as a trade good. Or it can also be repurposed as a huge rug.

A surprisingly clean animal dubbed the owl-bear by those that find them amusing as they attempt to fly by rapidly flapping their stubby vestigial wings. That is until they get their eyes pecked out and flattened by their weight.  An ursine hybrid with recessive avian genes. Slightly dumber but easier to train, they lay eggs every couple of days and have the strength to protect their clutch. Slower than a bear but their ability to hover over terrain means they perform better in harsh terrain.  <color=#E5E54C>Gameplay effect:</color> All primary bear hybrids have stun attacks. Although too heavy to fly, it can use its wings to nullify terrain movement costs.
Fertilized bearchicken egg. If all goes well, it should hatch into one of these abominations. It can be eaten raw, but it's much better cooked.
Unfertilized bearchicken egg. It can be eaten raw, but it's much, much better cooked.

A wonderful animal for those cold winter journeys, very popular as travellers snuggle into their fur at night to keep warm. Fights have even broken out over who gets to sleep with the oversized rug.  An ursine hybrid with recessive muffalo genes. Very filthy but a decently intelligent pack animal that produces good-quality wool and milk. Performs very well in cold environments and is more than capable of defending itself.  <color=#E5E54C>Gameplay effect:</color> All primary bear hybrids have stun attacks.
An strange blue cheese created from Bearffalo milk. Very nutritive, but very high in saturated fats.
Milk from a bearffalo. Quite high in fat content, and very nutritive.

While theyre surprisingly tireless when they have a home to rest at, these manned mares are quite reluctant to hurry along when made to carry loads in a caravan. Their bodys efficiency means theyll get a task done when it needs to, and not a moment sooner. What makes it worse is that theyre smart enough to know that theyre cute - and powerful - enough to get away with it.  An equine hybrid with recessive ursine genes. The inherent hibernating nature of bears has combined with the high energy of horses to create this particular hybrid that requires little in the way of rest and a much more efficient and versatile digestive system. They are quite a bit slower as a consequence, along with their higher body mass.  <color=#E5E54C>Gameplay effect:</color> All equine hybrids are good for caravaning. A caravan with one of them needs a shorter resting period, only stopping to rest between 23:30 PM and 4 AM.

A terrifying combination of the raw power of a bear and the intellect of a human, resulting in a creature that loves to abuse its prey. Not quite as strong due to the strange hand-paw shapes, but very energetic and eager to get their victims to catch these hands.  An ursine hybrid with recessive humanoid genes. Very high intellect but comparatively fragile compared to similar hybrids. Their bodies contain oversized and overstimulated adrenal glands that are found just under the surface of the skin, which can be regularly extracted for a substance analogous to Go-Juice.  <color=#E5E54C>Gameplay effect:</color> Humanoid hybrids will periodically engage other colonists in conversation, talking about a variety of topics. This increases the social recreation needs of those they interact with by 10% (subject to diminishing returns like all joy types). If using Ideology, humanoid hybrids are subject to precepts.

Not many people get to see a naked bear, and fewer still want a repeat viewing. This oversized mole-rat inspires plenty of fear with its massive teeth, but gets a lot of love and affection from those wanting a large, hairless pet that gnaws on the furniture.  An ursine hybrid with recessive rodent genes. Very slow both mentally and physically along with dietary restrictions, but very fierce in combat and immune to pain. Also they have the added benefit of having a short reproductive cycle, low metabolism and being completely fearless in hunting prey.  <color=#E5E54C>Gameplay effect:</color> All primary bear hybrids have stun attacks. No pain sensitivity. This hybrid won't be knocked down in combat due to pain.

The dinosaur nerds out there should love this hybrid. Got one hell of a nasty bite and even the claws will both knock you down and make you unable to get up. Often bred for hunting by the bored one percenters who want to eat massive drumsticks, caveman style.  A reptile hybrid with recessive ursine genes. Highly intelligent and an exceptional frontline trooper, with a venomous, stunning attack, fast movement speed and high health pool.  <color=#E5E54C>Gameplay effect:</color> All reptile hybrids have good temperature tolerance ranges and venomous attacks.

An absolute unit of an insectoid hybrid, this massive chubster is incredibly smart and hard to kill. All the excess blubber has been replaced with either chitin or muscle fibre, so dont go making comments about their bulk.  An insectoid hybrid with recessive ursine genes. Very thick armour plating and a calm temperament make this hybrid an excellent combat animal. Requires little in the way of retraining and can dish out respectable damage as well.  <color=#E5E54C>Gameplay effect:</color> All insectoid hybrids have good armor and no toxic sensitivity, but they are always sterile and can't reproduce, even if a fertility booster is used to create them.

Great care must be taken before considering raising this chonky boy, as they have a metabolism that matches their high ferocity and movement speed. Pretty useful in keeping egg-laying animal populations in check.  An ursine hybrid with recessive canine genes. A very fierce and intelligent combat hybrid with an incredible appetite. As they are almost constantly hungry, they will dig for berries when theyre hungry provided its growing season.  <color=#E5E54C>Gameplay effect:</color> All primary bear hybrids have stun attacks.

An incredibly quick - mentally and physically - hunter with an overactive castoreum gland, effectively allowing them to actively convert meat and trees into vegetables. Technically vegans should be fine with it since, much like bees, it needs to be harvested and the beaverwolf will absolutely let you know if it doesnt like you touching it.  A rodent hybrid with recessive canine genes. A very quick but cautious predator, this hybrid is both intelligent and frequently looking for its next meal. Able to freely roam and doesnt require a pen, they are both carnivorous and dendrovorous while also offering daily harvests of castoreum which functions as a vegetable in dishes.  <color=#E5E54C>Gameplay effect:</color> All rodent hybrids have fast gestation, as long as a fertility unblocker was used when creating them in the genomorpher.
Castoreum is a yellowish exudate from the castor sacs of beavers. It is historically used as a food additive and natural flavour, often as a substitute vanilla flavour.
An herb-like vegetable widely cultivated for humans and livestock alike, notably nutritious and historically used in dye making.

Light, slender, and quick-pointing never described a semi-auto better than the Benelli Montefeltro 20-gauge and 12-gauge shotgun. The Inertia Driven system in these Benelli shotguns requires no springs or gas cylinder under the forend. That allows the Montefeltros forend to be slim and graceful, while the lightweight, anodized aluminium receiver keeps weight to a minimum.

A shelf for storing miscellaneous items, from artillery shells to artwork, from bionic arms to bricks, from chairs to corpses.  It doesn't ask questions, it just stores things.  Items stored in this will not deteriorate, even if outside.  This shelf holds more than the regular one, and is not limited by weight (use your own judgement).
Fuel made from the processes of refining various types of plants for oils and alcohols. And is used to fuel generators and workbenches.

An advanced artificial arm with a built-in concussion effect designed for knocking down walls. Silenced mini-servos give great strength, while the biogel nerve-link gives exquisite control. A lattice-dust healing system allows it to recover from damage.

An advanced artificial leg with multiple built-in tools used in general cleaning work. Silenced mini-servos give great strength, while the biogel nerve-link gives exquisite control. A lattice-dust healing system allows it to recover from damage.

An advanced artificial arm with multiple built-in tools used in general construction work. Silenced mini-servos give great strength, while the biogel nerve-link gives exquisite control. A lattice-dust healing system allows it to recover from damage.

An advanced artificial arm with a built-in snake drill, which allows the miner to rapidly find and exploit weak lines in the rock. Silenced mini-servos give great strength, while the biogel nerve-link gives exquisite control. A lattice-dust healing system allows it to recover from damage.

An advanced artificial arm with multiple built-in telescopic finger-like protrusions that can simultaneously harvest from several points on the same plant, or precisely sow several holes at once. Silenced mini-servos give great strength, while the biogel nerve-link gives exquisite control. A lattice-dust healing system allows it to recover from damage.
An advanced artificial kidney. It has synthetic muscle fibers and a lattice-dust healing system. It is better than a biological kidney in almost every way.
An advanced artificial liver. It has synthetic muscle fibers and a lattice-dust healing system. It is better than a biological liver in almost every way.
An advanced artificial lung. It has synthetic muscle fibers and a lattice-dust healing system. It is better than a biological lung in almost every way.

An advanced artificial arm fitted with retractable power claw blades. Silenced mini-servos give great strength, while the biogel nerve-link gives exquisite control. A lattice-dust healing system allows it to recover from damage.
A work station for assembling and disassembling bionics.

A bulbous, tender, tasty purplish-black fruit of the nightshade family. Aubergines or eggplants are great in a variety of dishes, and the Black Beauty variety is delicious grilled, baked and stir-fried.
Blue colored berry that grows in bushes. Even good raw.

The Razor BM (Bullseye Modified) 003 is an upgraded version of the BM001 Razor, based on the Mark II Bullseye design the charge is more also more powerful. The tracking system of the rifle is more accurate for close-mid range targets outside of cover. It is for this reason the weapon earn its nickname "Blue Death".

A payload of boom genetic material. Can be used at the genomorpher to create a growth cell of a hybrid animal. This tier 1 genome can be used as either a primary or secondary genome.  <color=#E5E54C>Gameplay effect:</color> All boom hybrids explode on death. Farm hybrids produce chemfuel, while combat hybrids can use exploding abilities.  <color=#E5E54C>Extraction:</color> Can be extracted via the genome extractor table or any genome excavator from:

Directly injects boom genes in an humanoid. This genetrainer gives the ability to produce chemfuel like a boomalope.  Genetrainers are implants that do not take the place of any given organ. Only one can be "installed" at a time. Using a second genetrainer will have no effect. Bear in mind that a genetrainer modifies the genes of the human subject, and only death will get rid of its effects.

Originally intended as a way to make boomalopes more combat viable, their powerful muscles have instead been focused on compressing its produced chemfuel as a way to store greater amounts of chemfuel without care of how dangerous it is.  A boomalope hybrid with recessive ursine genes. Consumes more than twice as much compared to a boomalope but produces deepchem instead. Theyre also capable of defending themselves should any predator be foolish enough to go after them.

A biological weapon in compact form, these living, breathing, shitting bombs are ideally assembled into a massive horde and sent squawking at the enemy. Allegedly, this particular hybrid has been brought up in certain court cases as the original creator thought it would be funny to create lethal egg timers.  A boomalope hybrid with recessive avian genes. Produces edible eggs very slowly, but can lay a clutch of explosive eggs twice a day. Theyre both reasonably intelligent and quick on their feet.
Fertilized Boomachicken egg. If all goes well, it should hatch into one of these abominations. It can be eaten raw, but it's much better cooked.
Unfertilized Boomachicken egg. It can be eaten raw, but it's much, much better cooked.

While more of a risk to keep around, they are considerably more efficient and dont eat your crops as much. Plus their permanent sad expression just makes you want to pet them, how can you say no.  A perfect boomalope animal, paragon of all similar animals with no needless junk genetic data. Besides the various improvements to the baseline animals abilities, this paragon produces deepchem instead and explodes on death in a much more violent fashion.

Outright refuses to let anyone else milk them for their chemfuel as they view it as a violation of their humanoid rights. They make for a good conversation partner even if their stance can be a little volatile.  A boomalope hybrid with recessive humanoid genes. Instead of supplying a regular amount of chemfuel, this hybrid will syphon themselves to top up a limited number of machinery powered by chemfuel, such as generators and pod launchers.  <color=#E5E54C>Gameplay effect:</color> Humanoid hybrids will periodically engage other colonists in conversation, talking about a variety of topics. This increases the social recreation needs of those they interact with by 10% (subject to diminishing returns like all joy types). If using Ideology, humanoid hybrids are subject to precepts. Boomen periodically refuel some machines powered by chemfuel in a 10 tile radius (chemfuel generators and pod launchers).

For lovers of xenomorphs everywhere, this bomb-ass bombadier is ready to launch sacs of acidic chemfuel at your enemies for fun and profit. Dont expect a second pair of jaws though, that mouth is for spitting only.  An insectoid hybrid with recessive boomalope genes. Quite temperamental for a hybrid, but they prove to be worth it as they store caustic chemfuel in their sacs which can then be lobbed at a distance. Practically useless in melee, so keep them safe and provide fire support. Can be ordered to detonate auxiliary acid sacs as a defensive measure, but that will also self-harm.  <color=#E5E54C>Gameplay effect:</color> All insectoid hybrids have good armor and no toxic sensitivity, but they are always sterile and can't reproduce, even if a fertility booster is used to create them.

Combining the frequent nuzzling of a cat and the deepchem production of a primary boomalope hybrid is surely in no way going to end badly. Better not to ignore them should they complain loudly about wanting dinner.  A boomalope hybrid with recessive feline genes. They make for an interesting companion for those who desire chemfuel production but also want to be able to cuddle said creatures. They can also be butchered to retrieve an internal gland filled with deepchem.  <color=#E5E54C>Gameplay effect:</color> Like all cat hybrids, they have an improved melee dodge ability and a short nuzzle period.

People love efficiency and having one thing to cover all their needs. Well this isnt it, but it gets damn close. The chemfuel sacs have mixed with milk-producing glands, which make for a milk that smells like pure gasoline and could almost power a vehicle.  A boomalope hybrid with recessive muffalo genes. Has a large appetite due to it producing multiple products, namely deepchem, thin wool and an unusual milk that shares properties with Chemshine.

Inherently less effective at refining chemfuel when allowed to rest at its leisure while also being a good pack animal and riding companion. During distant travels, the long periods of engagement for their muscles actively puts their glands into overdrive. Quite effective should there be a vehicle that uses chemfuel, but dont ask how that would work out. Maybe its the desire to compete against machinery or knowing that if the vehicle breaks down it's gonna have to do all that bloody walking again.  An equine hybrid with recessive boomalope genes. While they are comparatively slower, their inherent need to exercise means that their capability in producing chemfuel is severely hampered if their muscles arent engaged for long periods of time. When travelling as part of a caravan, their chemfuel production speed is effectively quadrupled.  <color=#E5E54C>Gameplay effect:</color> All equine hybrids are good for caravaning. A caravan with one of them needs a shorter resting period, only stopping to rest between 23:30 PM and 4 AM.

An improvised explosive trap built out of... best if you don't think about it. Cannot be placed adjacent to other traps. Animals can sense these when calm. Less potent than regular high-explosive shell traps.

What happens when you mix a spitting cobra, a rattlesnake and a creature designed to lactate refined fuel? This abomination, thats what. Drive it into a corner and itll hurt itself to release deadly neurotoxins. Try and keep your distance and itll spit toxic blood right at you. Clearly someone was a sore loser in playing pretend games as a child, but had either the brains or the money to prove themselves right.  A reptile hybrid with recessive boomalope genes. Decently intelligent with a nasty bite and even nastier ranged attack, both causing toxic buildup. Quite a high metabolism which supports its various combat abilities, best suited for home defence.  <color=#E5E54C>Gameplay effect:</color> All reptile hybrids have good temperature tolerance ranges and venomous attacks.

With adorable horns and long snoots, these squeaky lads are ideal in giving your enemy a stunning surprise. Their chemfuel mixture includes other gases that create a blinding and disorienting flashbang when remotely detonated. Theyll still make a regular boom if killed though.  A boomalope hybrid with recessive rodent genes. Quite fast and intelligent, these hybrids work as excellent swarm attackers. Their rapid reproduction cycle and stunning explosion make for an ideal companion to ranged masters.

For those who wished they could equip their canines with explosive vests, the Boomwolf stores pressurised - almost solidified - chemfuel which can be remotely discharged as a non-explosive gas. Thanks to thermodynamics, it is extremely cold upon release and can just as easily hurt the hybrid as well as everything nearby.  A boomalope hybrid with recessive canine genes. Very intelligent, fast and dangerous, they make for an interesting combat animal. One of the few canine-type hybrids that work better solo than as a pack.
A bowl of slow cooking stew.   Food Effects: Consciousness, Metabolism, Blood Filtration, and Blood Pumping.
A very simple baked good. Since thousands of years humans bake and eat these tasty loafs.
A brown coloured cheese, similar in taste to Cheddar but with roasted nut overtones. Not very nutritive, but very pleasurable to eat.

Brown sugar is a sucrose sugar product with a distinctive brown color due to the presence of sugarcane molasses, and it adds a much desired sweetness. Sugar is easily converted into energy by the body, which may result in a nice burst of energy.

The C14 Timberwolf MRSWS (Medium Range Sniper Weapon System) is a bolt-action sniper rifle built by the Canadian arms company PGW Defence Technologies Inc. In 2005 they won the contract to supply the Canadian Forces Land Command with the C14 Timberwolf MRSWS for $4.5 million.  The military version of the rifle, which is being used to replace the C3A1 sniper rifle, started as a civilian precision sport rifle. The military rifle, however, has several modifications to make it better suited for military use, and many accessories are available.  The official military designation for the rifle is C14 Timberwolf Medium Range Sniper Weapon System (MRSWS).

The Colt Canada C7 is a Canadian assault rifle, manufactured by Colt Canada (formerly Diemaco prior to 2005), a variant of the Armalite AR-15, and having similar design and function to the Colt M16A3.  The C7 and its variants have been adopted as the standard issue rifle by the militaries of Canada, Norway (Special forces only), Denmark and the Netherlands. Following trials, C8 variants are general issue firearms for the United Kingdom's Special Forces And it is the standard firearm of the Dutch Airforce (C8A1) and other specialist users within the British military. It has been utilized in various combat deployments by Canadian, British, Norwegian, Dutch and Danish Forces in Afghanistan and Iraq.

The L119A1 / L119A2 Special Forces Individual Weapon (SFIW) (known commercially as the C8 CQB or C8A2) is a carbine in widespread use by United Kingdom Special Forces (UKSF).  The C8 Canadian-made weapons serve as the standard assault rifle for the UKSF, replacing the venerable M16 in that role. The weapons were initially manufactured by Diemaco, who have since become Colt Canada. The C8A2 carbine is very similar to the C8, but having a cold-hammer forged heavy 368-millimetre (14.5 in) barrel (as opposed to the 14.5-inch pencil-profile barrel) and a flat-top upper receiver.
A somewhat hardy, leafy green vegetable, often chopped and then fermented or stewed.
Raw cactus fruit.

A payload of canine genetic material. Can be used at the genomorpher to create a growth cell of a hybrid animal. This tier 1 genome can be used as either a primary or secondary genome.  <color=#E5E54C>Gameplay effect:</color> All primary canine hybrids have the adrenaline rush ability. All canine hybrids have fast attack speed.  <color=#E5E54C>Extraction:</color> Can be extracted via the genome extractor table or any genome excavator from:

Directly injects canine genes in an humanoid. This genetrainer gives the wolf speed health state, increasing movement speed, eating speed and immunity gain speed.  Genetrainers are implants that do not take the place of any given organ. Only one can be "installed" at a time. Using a second genetrainer will have no effect. Bear in mind that a genetrainer modifies the genes of the human subject, and only death will get rid of its effects.

An improved version of mans best friend, easier to train, more assertive and dangerous to those that threaten a household. Sadly, far too proud to admit it really wants a belly rub.  A perfect canine animal, paragon of all similar animals with no needless junk genetic data. Besides the various improvements to the baseline animals abilities, this paragon can be slaughtered for a valuable pelt, which can either be used for decoration or sold.

Boiled eggs vacuum sealed and secured in a steel can effectively extending shelf life indefinitely. While edible cold right out of the can it's far more nourishing mixed into a meal and heated.  Canned goods are intended as a way to preserve food and use it an an ingredient later, not as a final meal.

Fish vacuum sealed and secured in a steel can effectively extending shelf life indefinitely. While edible cold right out of the can it's far more nourishing mixed into a meal and heated.  Canned goods are intended as a way to preserve food and use it an an ingredient later, not as a final meal.

Cooked and preserved fruit in a hermetically sealed, durable container. Preserved food lasts indefinitely without refrigeration.  Fruit differs from produce in that it is specifically required in the production of desserts.  Canned goods are intended as a way to preserve food and use it an an ingredient later, not as a final meal.

Meat vacuum sealed and secured in a steel can effectively extending shelf life indefinitely. While edible cold right out of the can it's far more nourishing mixed into a meal and heated.  Canned goods are intended as a way to preserve food and use it an an ingredient later, not as a final meal.

Produce vacuum sealed and secured in a steel can effectively extending shelf life indefinitely. While edible cold right out of the can it's far more nourishing mixed into a meal and heated.  Canned goods are intended as a way to preserve food and use it an an ingredient later, not as a final meal.
A canning machine is an appliance to store preserved food inside metallic cans. Each canning operation needs a certain amount of Steel.
A sweet candy made from sugar and milk.   Food Effects: Moving.
a mold case for casting metal parts. the mold shape is engraving at art table and place in a wooden box filled with sand.

Have you ever wanted to have a cat that could start fires with hairballs? No? Too bad, this one does and if youre unlucky itll be outside when its hunting. Which wont be often, because those fuel sacs make for a surprisingly efficient energy reserve. Exploding kittens is no longer just a game, its a hazard warning.  A feline hybrid with recessive boomalope genes. Intelligent, low maintenance with a weak ranged flame attack, they make for an unusual companion.   <color=#E5E54C>Gameplay effect:</color> Like all cat hybrids, they have an improved melee dodge ability, which in the case of these small animals is ideal to get out of a fight.

The perfect companion in compact form, this tiny terror is willing to throw down with its surprising bulk. And good lord, what an affectionate beefcake.  A feline hybrid with recessive ursine genes. Can both take and dish out punishment disproportionate to its size while being clever enough to actively hunt for prey not much larger than itself. Incredibly easy to train and will intermittently dig up burrowed rats.  <color=#E5E54C>Gameplay effect:</color> Like all cat hybrids, they have an improved melee dodge ability, which in the case of these small animals is ideal to get out of a fight. Stunning attacks like bear hybrids.

This smart little shit knows where to kick so it hurts, and thats often the eyes. The unusual genetic makeup has made their claws as long as a human thumb, so best to pet it when it wants to and avoid touching the belly.  A feline hybrid with recessive avian genes. A little slow for its size, it makes for a vicious attack animal if it can be permitted to get in melee range. Be careful as it cant take much punishment.  <color=#E5E54C>Gameplay effect:</color> Like all cat hybrids, they have an improved melee dodge ability, which in the case of these small animals is ideal to get out of a fight. Go for the eyes: Catchicken attacks have a 25% chance to affect the victim's eyes.

Someone couldnt bear being separated from their trusty feline companions when away on trips. So they decided to make one that everyone would want to take with them on long journeys. Also they look incredibly adorable with their little baggies.  A feline hybrid with recessive muffalo genes. While not great as a pack animal, they make for a fantastic caravaning companion as they will actively forage for prey during trips. This creates a stacking effect of boosting the amount of food foraged for every other catffalo in the trip. Theyre quite hardy too but should be kept away from combat.  <color=#E5E54C>Gameplay effect:</color> Like all cat hybrids, they have an improved melee dodge ability, which in the case of these small animals is ideal to get out of a fight. Forages for small prey while caravaning, increasing the amount of foraged food by 10% (and it stacks per catffalo on the caravan!).

Tell me, do you want a cat large enough to ride at speeds that would be illegal on most urbworld city streets? Of course you do, and if you say otherwise youre a coward. This ferocious feline is ready to tear up the track and hunt prey comically smaller than itself. Theyre also incredibly smart and have a tendency to stalk their owners when their backs are turned. Dont worry though, it only wants to pin you down and drown you in fur and saliva.  An equine hybrid with recessive feline genes. Quite durable and combat capable for a pack animal, they can be drafted to execute at-will pouncing to close distance with the enemy. They are only slightly less effective as horses in riding but have better stamina, in exchange they are pure carnivores so their diet can be rather restrictive.  <color=#E5E54C>Gameplay effect:</color> All equine hybrids are good for caravaning. A caravan with one of them needs a shorter resting period, only stopping to rest between 23:30 PM and 4 AM. Like all cat hybrids, they have an improved melee dodge ability, making them perfect for the front lines, and a short nuzzle period. Always starts as draftable, even if not using a controller booster to create it. Pounce ability: when drafted, the player can use the pounce ability to make the hybrid jump around. The ability can be triggered every 2 hours.

Just the sweetest little kitty cat youll ever encounter, they were bred as tiny caretakers to look after people in hospital wards. Despite being a health violation, they were extremely popular with the infirms as they not only fed patients but also engaged in conversation and gave friendly headbutts. It is also alleged that their purring helped broken bones heal quicker, but no conclusive evidence has been shown.  A feline hybrid with recessive humanoid genes. Quite slow and fragile, comparatively speaking, with a low damage output and lower hunger rate. However, they make for very good bedside companions for the ill and will regularly feed those that cannot feed themselves.  <color=#E5E54C>Gameplay effect:</color> Humanoid hybrids will periodically engage other colonists in conversation, talking about a variety of topics. This increases the social recreation needs of those they interact with by 10% (subject to diminishing returns like all joy types). If using Ideology, humanoid hybrids are subject to precepts. Catmen are compassionate animals that will help with feeding medical patients around the colony.

Everyone can agree that cats and rabbits have incredibly soft fur, so can you imagine how cute and fluffy they would be if you mixed their traits together? They also love to be pet multiple times a day, so everyone can get in on this pet so fluffy it's to die for.  A feline hybrid with recessive rodent genes. While a somewhat independent carnivore, this hybrid is ideal inside a colony as it not only provides a  non-stacking mood boost to those nearby from its cuteness, but it also nuzzles every few hours. Theyre also very fast breeders.  <color=#E5E54C>Gameplay effect:</color> Like all cat hybrids, they have an improved melee dodge ability, which in the case of these small animals is ideal to get out of a fight. Gives non-stacking +3 mood to everyone in a 8 tiles radius.

For some reason people really want cats to be able to carry stuff, depicted often in consumer media. Well this palico should have you sorted, however despite numerous efforts it has proved impossible to train them in using brooms.  A feline hybrid with recessive canine genes. An incredibly fast hauling companion that can also defend itself, these creatures borne forth from pop culture are incredibly smart and incredibly clean. They cant carry much, but having a whole army wont cause your base to fill with filth, just the normal degenerates.  <color=#E5E54C>Gameplay effect:</color> Like all cat hybrids, they have an improved melee dodge ability, which in the case of these small animals is ideal to get out of a fight. Produces (and spreads) absolutely no filth.
Cools a room by circulating air. Includes a built-in lamp.
Cools a room by circulating air. Includes a built-in lamp.

A chainsaw (or chain saw) is a portable gasoline-, electric-, or battery-powered saw that cuts with a set of teeth attached to a rotating chain driven along a guide bar. It is used in activities such as tree felling, limbing, bucking, pruning, cutting firebreaks in wildland fire suppression, and harvesting of firewood. Chainsaws with specially designed bar-and-chain combinations have been developed as tools for use in chainsaw art and chainsaw mills.  This brand is of the ECHO line of industrial chainsaws and helps with plant work speed.
A doormat to clean your feet.

Cheese is a dairy product, derived from milk and produced in a wide range of flavors, textures and forms by coagulation of the milk protein casein. Cheese is valued for its portability, long life, and high content of fat, protein, calcium, and phosphorus. It is more compact and has a longer shelf life than milk.
A block of cheese.
Two slices of bread with grilled meat and cheese melt.   Food Effects: Metabolism and Manipulation.

A cheese press is a device for pressing whey from curds when making cheese. Pressing influences the cheese's hardness and texture and will also determine the shape of the block or wheel of cheese. This press also works as a ripening chamber, so the longer the cheese is left ripening, the higher its quality will be.
A red berry fruit that grows on trees.

For something so small, this animal has a hell of an appetite. Lacking in many departments, but the nutrition has to go somewhere and thats for those looking for a non-vegan friendly option of getting high. The person who thought it would be a good idea to inhale the burning feathers of this plump creature is one stoners everywhere praise while they blaze.  An avian hybrid with recessive ursine genes. Has a considerably larger appetite and inherent wildness, but reproduces quickly.  <color=#E5E54C>Gameplay effect:</color> Can be regularly plucked for chickenbear feathers. When these feathers are turned into powder at a Drug lab, they can be rolled into a joint to be smoked.
Fertilized Chickenbear egg. If all goes well, it should hatch into one of these abominations. It can be eaten raw, but it's much better cooked.
Unfertilized Chickenbear egg. It can be eaten raw, but it's much, much better cooked.
Chickenbear feathers can be gathered and processed into a fine powder called featherdust, which produces a mild euphoric sensation when burned and inhaled.

Respectably intelligent as well as lethal, these egg-laying, plump beasties love nuzzling their owners and biting their enemies. Sometimes those are different people.  An avian hybrid with recessive feline genes. Quite clean with a low gestation period, they make for an average farm animal and an average combatant with good speed. They still require a pen, so they make for good home defence.  <color=#E5E54C>Gameplay effect:</color> Like all cat hybrids, they have an improved melee dodge ability and a short nuzzle period.
Fertilized Chickencat egg. If all goes well, it should hatch into one of these abominations. It can be eaten raw, but it's much better cooked.
Unfertilized Chickencat egg. It can be eaten raw, but it's much, much better cooked.

You wouldnt think something so small could eat so much, but thats the price you pay for the sake of convenience. That convenience is sporadic, low in nutrition and very thin, an effect commonly described as nerfing.  An avian hybrid with recessive muffalo genes. Loves to wander so it must be securely penned, but they make for a surprising pack beast. Capable of producing the holy trinity of milk, eggs and wool, however they can be quite lacking in substance.
A very bland, almost tasteless cheese. The only good thing about it is that it ripens much faster than other cheeses.
Fertilized Chickenffalo egg. If all goes well, it should hatch into one of these abominations. It can be eaten raw, but it's much better cooked.
Unfertilized Chickenffalo egg. It can be eaten raw, but it's much, much better cooked.
Milk from a chickenffalo. Looks like watered down milk. Probably not much better than water.

An agile avian that most people expect to be more yellow in colour and go wark every now and then. A delightfully speedy mount that can pull off some impressive turns, this hybrid has been bred even further with other species to make for more colourful and genetically stable bird mounts. Some speculate that this particular creature is the original ancestor of the Ave, while the Royal Ave came from those that were bred more for plumage than performance.  An equine hybrid with recessive avian genes. Comparatively smaller than a purebred, but incredibly fast both in a singular location and as part of a caravan. A rather unusual hybrid in that it reproduces very slowly in a safe, similar environment, however this changes on caravan trips. Constant new sights and experiences puts their reproductive cycle into overdrive as it tries to spread its species over a broad horizon, however these eggs are genetically sterile so that they instead provide a healthy protein supplement for those who can only gather fruits and vegetables.  <color=#E5E54C>Gameplay effect:</color> All equine hybrids are good for caravaning. A caravan with one of them needs a shorter resting period, only stopping to rest between 23:30 PM and 4 AM.
Fertilized chickenhorse egg. If all goes well, it should hatch into one of these abominations. It can be eaten raw, but it's much better cooked.
Unfertilized chickenhorse egg. It can be eaten raw, but it's much, much better cooked.

Chickens are basically an evolution of dinosaurs, so someone decided to turn them back. Unfortunately they didnt exactly bother to check that they should still be avian rather than reptilian, so it resulted in this nasty little thing that reproduces at an insane rate and empties your fridge. But hey, theyll spit on your enemies and their right to shit everywhere, especially where they eat.  A reptile hybrid with recessive avian genes. This particular farm animal is smart enough that it doesnt need a pen and breeds faster than other reptiles. A very large appetite for a creature so small, which supports its ability to spit out nasty toxins on their enemies and create messes on the floor. Very easy to train and has a good memory.  <color=#E5E54C>Gameplay effect:</color> All reptile hybrids have good temperature tolerance ranges and venomous attacks.
Fertilized chickenlizard egg. If all goes well, it should hatch into one of these abominations. It can be eaten raw, but it's much better cooked.
Unfertilized chickenlizard egg. It can be eaten raw, but it's much, much better cooked.

The ideal companion for those who love the smell of fried eggs and napalm in the morning. Regretfully theyre far too birdbrained to receive any direction, and most owners have been noted saying Ive made a huge mistake.  An avian hybrid with recessive boomalope genes. Very dangerous if allowed to breed uncontrollably, so consider liberal fireproofing and selling the excess. Produces chemfuel daily as well as an egg every 2 days.
Fertilized Chickenlope egg. If all goes well, it should hatch into one of these abominations. It can be eaten raw, but it's much better cooked.
Unfertilized Chickenlope egg. It can be eaten raw, but it's much, much better cooked.

One of the few unusual animal hybrids that come with their own warning labels despite being almost entirely harmless. All it took was one absent-minded vegan to cause a single couple of Breeders to overpopulate and devastate the ecology of an entire continent. Fairy tales surrounding the fluffy terror have done nothing to help it be taken seriously.  An avian hybrid with recessive rodent genes. An incredibly low metabolism coupled with an incredibly high reproduction rate, these animals are very sensitive to temperature and are unusually keen on escaping to the wilds.

Fertilized Chickenrabbit egg. If all goes well, it should hatch into one of these abominations. It can be eaten raw, but it's much better cooked. The colonists swear it was coloured like this when the animal laid it.
Unfertilized Chickenrabbit egg. It can be eaten raw, but it's much, much better cooked. The colonists swear it was coloured like this when the animal laid it.

For the unusual connoisseur who both enjoys a healthy breakfast and the feel of silk pyjamas. A very niche market, but considering the amount of money paid for the development, people like that are too rich to be considered mad. Theyre simply eccentric with refined tastes, or tossers as the disenfranchised call them.  An insectoid hybrid with recessive avian genes. Quite large and difficult to train for an animal that lays eggs, this particular hybrid should always be kept warm due to the various functions taking up valuable space. Capable of producing not only eggs but also valuable silk, and is protected by thin, flexible scales to resist cuts.  <color=#E5E54C>Gameplay effect:</color> All insectoid hybrids have good armor and no toxic sensitivity, but they are always sterile and can't reproduce, even if a fertility booster is used to create them.
Unfertilized Chickenspider egg. It can be eaten raw, but it's much, much better cooked. Since insectoid hybrids are always infertile, these eggs can never be fertilized.

The Tiny Terror with a disconcertingly large mouth and sharp teeth. These comic flightless web-footed little bastards may finally unwittingly help man to fathom the uncharted depths of just how dangerous they can make a living creature the size of a basketball.  An avian hybrid with recessive canine genes. Doesnt produce much in the way of eggs but makes up for it by having a shorter gestation period and a very nasty bite. Theyre also incredibly smart and agile, making them ideal for swarm tactics.
Fertilized Chickenwolf egg. If all goes well, it should hatch into one of these abominations. It can be eaten raw, but it's much better cooked.
Unfertilized Chickenwolf egg. It can be eaten raw, but it's much, much better cooked.
Chocolate added to milk.
A mixture of cocoa, water and sugar, forming a bitter-sweet pourable syrup, perfect for coating desserts. While still not good for you, chocolate syrup is not quite as bad as straight sugar.
A pack of cigarillos
A covered rack for storing clothing for easy, quick access and a tidy room.
A sweet fruit that grows on vines.
A coconut fruit that grows on trees. Has a hard outer shell with a juicy fruit flesh inside.
Raw Coffee. Best prepared as a beverage

A payload of colossal genetic material. Can be used at the genomorpher to create a growth cell of a hybrid animal. This tier 3 genome can only be used as primary genome.  <color=#E5E54C>Gameplay effect:</color> Extreme increase in size, health, damage and market value at the cost of slower attack speed.  <color=#E5E54C>Extraction:</color> Can only be extracted via an archotech genome excavator from:

Directly injects colossal genes in an humanoid. This genetrainer gives the animal empathy health state, making the subject much more efficient when dealing with animals.  Genetrainers are implants that do not take the place of any given organ. Only one can be "installed" at a time. Using a second genetrainer will have no effect. Bear in mind that a genetrainer modifies the genes of the human subject, and only death will get rid of its effects.

The gigantic, graceful creature has somehow been improved even further, proving infallibly that theres always a taller mountain. Significantly easier to train and with a more efficient digestive system, this creature is possibly how the thrumbo originally was when first bred in a lab before it got tainted through terraforming.  A perfect colossal animal, paragon of all similar animals with no needless junk genetic data. Besides the various improvements to the baseline animals abilities, this paragon makes for an excellent mount for caravans and can forcibly rush itself, getting faster and creating dust clouds that impede ranged attacks.

The Colt Cobra is a lightweight, aluminum-framed, double-action short-barrelled revolver, not to be confused with the Colt King Cobra.    The Cobra was chambered in .38 Special, .38 New police, .32 Colt New Police, and .22 LR. It holds six shots of ammunition and was sold by Colt from 1950 until 1981.

The Colt Python is a .357 Magnum caliber revolver formerly manufactured by Colt's Manufacturing Company of Hartford, Connecticut. It is sometimes referred to as a "Combat Magnum". It was first introduced in 1955, the same year as Smith and Wesson's M29 .44 Magnum.    Now discontinued, the Colt Python was intended for the premium revolver market segment.

One of mankind's oldest manufactured objects. The knife has taken many forms, but the concept has always remained the same: A handle for holding and a sharp edge for cutting.  This combat knife is of the Boker Plus M3 Trench Knife variant.

One of mankind's oldest manufactured objects. The knife has taken many forms, but the concept has always remained the same: A handle for holding and a sharp edge for cutting.  This combat knife is of the Eickhorn Recondo IV variant.

One of mankind's oldest manufactured objects. The knife has taken many forms, but the concept has always remained the same: A handle for holding and a sharp edge for cutting.  This combat knife is of the KABAR variant.

One of mankind's oldest manufactured objects. The knife has taken many forms, but the concept has always remained the same: A handle for holding and a sharp edge for cutting.  This combat knife is of the M9 Bayonet variant.
A working table to cut, slice and prepare condiments used in gourmet recipes.

Self-assembling machinery that fuses with the specimens nerve centers during the growth process. Effectively allows hybrids to be drafted but increases the chance of failure due to introduction of invasive foreign material.
Fresh baked cookies!   Food Effects: Well Fed: Baked Good.    Increased Consciousness and Metabolism
Increases work speed 14%. Needs to be placed near cooking tops. Will boost the cook speed of all tables near by.
A wide-barreled core bolt launcher designed for use on battle droids. It fires superheated bolts of plasma with an explosive core that explode upon impact.

This tremendous grub holds the dubious honor of "most disgusting creature in space." Chewing through solid stone and leaving a tunnel lubricated by its own slime, the cosmopillar was originally engineered as the vanguard of a hive of asteroid-mining insects. The project has long since been abandoned, but all throughout the Rim, asteroid miners live in fear of hungry cosmopillars.  Rumors persist that the oldest cosmopillars enter a deep hibernation at the center of asteroids, where their unstable genetics cause them to pupate into something even more terrible...
Raw meat from a manchicken. Unbelievably tasty, and unbelievably unethical. Light, nutritive and with no poisoning chance.

A rather muscular hybrid with an impressively long snout, this ravenous reptile combines adaptability with mobility. Unusually, its terrifyingly long maw filled with curved teeth is not used to tear flesh to eat but to imbue toxins and the required muscles to spray those toxins out. This means they have to eat a lot more due to their subpar digestive system and their favourite activities include lounging in the sun and moving with disturbing quickness when the dinner bell is sounded. Also it kinda looks like a weird shoe if you look at it, but, uh, dont put your foot in there.  An equine hybrid with recessive reptile genes. A rather slow hybrid for its category, its main advantage is that it is very durable and it has a ranged toxic breath attack. Quite durable and comfortable in a wide range of temperatures, they present a hidden danger for those foolish enough to attack an otherwise easy target.  <color=#E5E54C>Gameplay effect:</color> All equine hybrids are good for caravaning. A caravan with one of them needs a shorter resting period, only stopping to rest between 23:30 PM and 4 AM.

CZ BREN is a series of assault rifles, namely the CZ 805 BREN, CZ 807 and CZ BREN 2, created by esk zbrojovka Uhersk Brod in 2006 to replace the Sa vz. 58 in the Czech Army.   In November 2016, the Czech Army received its first batch of CZ BREN 2 next generation assault rifles.
The cuttings from the dandelion flower. Can be used in cooking or made into a healthy medicinal tea.

A fragrant tea infused with leaves of the dandelion plant. Drinking it induces a mild boosted immunity effect. This tea is easy to produce at cooking facilities.  Many tribes use dandelion tea as part of social and religious rituals.

A low-intelligent microcomputer that integrates seamlessly with the user's visual cortex, automatically adjusting the incoming light to a darklight spectrum.  This ensures that users who are accustomed to darklight conditions can venture into brightly lit areas without discomfort or visual impairment.
A sweet fruit that grows on trees.

The M4 carbine is a shorter and lighter variant of the M16A2 assault rifle. The M4 is a 5.5645mm NATO, air-cooled, direct impingement gas-operated, magazine-fed carbine. It has a 14.5 in (370 mm) barrel and a telescoping stock.  The M4 carbine is extensively used by the United States Armed Forces and is largely replacing the M16 rifle in United States Army and United States Marine Corps combat units as the primary infantry weapon and service rifle.  This M4 is the Daniel Defense M4 V11 variant.

Fish tenderized then filleted, then rolled in a thick batter before being submerged in hot oil and fried. The end result is a crunchy, unhealthy yet tasty soul food - Not quite as filling as a meal, but very pleasing to eat. Deep frying meats in this matter reduces shelf life as well unless frozen

Meat tenderized then filleted, then rolled in a thick batter before being submerged in hot oil and fried. The end result is a crunchy, unhealthy yet tasty soul food - Not quite as filling as a meal, but very pleasing to eat. Deep frying meats in this matter reduces shelf life as well unless frozen.

Vegetables julienned then patted dry before being dunked into hot oil until golden brown. As crispy and pleasing as they are, these deep fried treats are not as filling as a normal meal, nor as healthy. Deep frying vegetables in this matter reduces shelf life as well unless frozen.

A deep fryer is a kitchen appliance used for deep frying. Deep frying is a method of cooking by submerging food into oil at high heat, typically between temperatures of 350 F and 375 F (175 C to 190 C).
A very volatile sludge with a tar-like appearance. Can be used defensively or converted to regular chemfuel in a refinery.

The MRI Desert Eagle is a semi-automatic handgun notable for chambering the largest centerfire cartridge of any magazine-fed, self-loading pistol. Magnum Research Inc. (MRI) designed and developed the Desert Eagle. The design was refined and the pistols were manufactured by Israel Military Industries until 1995, when MRI shifted the manufacturing contract to Saco Defense in Saco, Maine. In 1998, MRI moved manufacturing back to IMI, which later commercialized its small arms branch under the name Israel Weapon Industries.

The design of the HTI is largely based on the SRS-A1, scaled up to handle larger cartridges.  Barrels on the HTI can be changed within 60 seconds, allowing the chambering to be easily changed or worn out barrels to be quickly replaced. The chamberings currently available from Desert Tech are .375 Cheyenne Tactical (CheyTac), .408 CheyTac, .416 Barrett and .50 BMG.  The bullpup design means the action is behind the trigger. As with all bullpups, this allows for a shorter overall length, without having to reduce barrel length.

The Desert Tech Stealth Recon Scout (SRS) is a bolt-action sniper rifle developed by the Utah-based firearm manufacturer Desert Tech (formerly Desert Tactical Arms). It was unveiled at the 2008 SHOT Show. It is known for its bullpup design.  A shorter variant of the SRS, called the SRS Covert, shares all the same features of the SRS, but uses shorter barrels and therefore a shorter handguard.
This huge egg is filled with unstable chemicals. It is going to explode!

A drug for preventing parasites and worms before they take hold. Blocks gut worms and muscle parasites. Must be taken every five days to remain effective.  This drug only prevents new parasites. It does not cure existing parasites - even those that are not yet discovered.

An extremely high tech glitterworld concoction, unsafe to drink directly due to bitter taste and a mild case of intraventricular hemorrhaging. However, when cooked properly into food, these effects inexplicably seem nullified. Any pawns with this present upon death will immediately be revived as if by miracle.

A vital piece of archotechnology that is part of the process in creating an Archocentipede.  This machine is able to extract genetic material from live hybrids and stores it for later use, preventing deterioration. Depending on the base Genoframe, the amount of viable genetic material extracted will vary.  Each storage bank can only store the genetic material from a single animal branch, such as ursine or feline. Inserting a hybrid into the database yields half as much valuable data compared to a paragon. DNA storage banks need to be in line of sight of the archocentipede former to connect to it properly.  Detailed yields for paragons (half for hybrids):  Awful quality: yields 1% Poor quality: yields 3% Normal quality: yields 6% Good quality: yields 12% Excellent quality: yields 25% Masterwork quality: yields 50% Legendary quality: yields 100%

Mans best friend who is also himself? Have you ever thought that the folds on a dogs skin can act almost as pockets? What if those folds held a knife and the dog could wield it? Well look no further, as this pup will answer those questions with violence.  A canine hybrid with recessive humanoid genes. A smart hybrid capable of holding conversations with their technical superiors and will sometimes obey commands to slaughter other tamed colony animals.  <color=#E5E54C>Gameplay effect:</color> Humanoid hybrids will periodically engage other colonists in conversation, talking about a variety of topics. This increases the social recreation needs of those they interact with by 10% (subject to diminishing returns like all joy types). If using Ideology, humanoid hybrids are subject to precepts. Dogmen will periodically obey commands to slaughter other colony (tamed) animals.
A doormat to clean your feet.
A doormat to clean your feet.
A doormat to clean your feet.
A doormat to clean your feet.
A doormat to clean your feet.
A doormat to clean your feet.

The Dragunov sniper rifle is a semi-automatic sniper/designated marksman rifle chambered in 7.6254mmR and developed in the Soviet Union.  The Dragunov was designed as a squad support weapon since, according to Soviet and Soviet-derived military doctrines, the long-range engagement ability was lost to ordinary troops when submachine guns and assault rifles (which are optimized for close-range and medium-range, rapid-fire combat) were adopted. For that reason, it was originally named "Self-Loading Rifle, System of Dragunov, Model of the Year 1963".
Fruit the has had the water removed.

A race of rudimentary humanlike worker robots.  Usually found toiling around in colonies around the rim which got a resident tinkerer.  Not capable of sapience, however their relative cheap cost and ability to work around the clock make them valuable workers.
A kit containing a disassembled Droid with all the tools required to assemble it.
Consumable batteries compatible for use for Androids and Droids.
A portable chemfuel generator which can be worn by Droids and Androids alike. Lasts for days on a single tank.

A automatic fabricator when supplied with power and materials will assemble a Droid. Droids are soulless automatons perfect for dumb labor and guard duty due to not needing to rest and partake in sapient tasks.
A repair kit containing the tools and materials, to fully restore a Droid to mint condition, from wear and tear to missing parts. Also refills coolant on Droids and Androids.  Used as a operation.
Miscellanous droid parts, adhesives, solder, welding resources & metal plates for repairing droids.
A long duster coat for blocking the sun and grit of the desert. Now with solarpanels for long journeys and passive power generation at home.
Produces a variable amount of heating units for radiators and hot water tanks. Manually controlled power setting. Can be controlled by thermostats.
A small electric-powered grinding stone for quickly grinding raw plants. Faster then the Grindstone. Larger capacity.
A electric oven used for baking.

An electric pot, also called a thermo pot, is a small appliance used for boiling water and maintaining it at a constant temperature. It is typically used to simmer soup over an extended period of time. Ingredients are submerged in water and left to cook over an extended period, allowing the flavors of the ingredients to gradually deepen and blend over time.  Soup on an unpowered electric pot will spoil extremely rapidly. Beware of solar flares!

A relatively small machine designed to simulate the environment of a mothers womb. Once a Growthcell has been inserted, the embryo can start growing all the way to its adult life stage before being released. Provides limited growing room for specimens.  <color=#E5E54C>Gameplay notes:</color> This electrowomb is very cheap to build, but will produce a failure if the inserted creature has a body size bigger than 1.

A small internal module designed to protect other bionics from electrical surges typically caused by EMP devices or lightning.  Upon detecting a power surge, the unit forcibly shuts down all bionics temporary to protect them.  The sudden abrupt disconnection causes the user to experience a loss of balance and momentarily confusion causing them to forget what they were doing.
A torpedo tipped with an EMP generator. Can be fired from torpedo tubes. Explodes when damaged.
a Four-stroke engine with optimum fuel conversion, it is the heart of an industrial world.
A small ultratech device which entangles itself with matter inside distant stars, essential to the function of the Johnson-Tanaka drive. It cannot be duplicated without glitterworld infrastructure.

A small internal module connected to the respiratory system that filters the incoming air of environmental toxins and gases.  The gathered toxins are later harmlessly excreted from the body.  The implant allows the user to survive longer in polluted environments.  Additionally, it negates the irritation of acidic smoke and prevents lung rot.

A payload of equine genetic material. Can be used at the genomorpher to create a growth cell of a hybrid animal. This tier 2 genome can only be used as primary genome.  <color=#E5E54C>Gameplay effect:</color> All equine hybrids have increased caravaning speed.  <color=#E5E54C>Extraction:</color> Can only be extracted via any genome excavator from:

Directly injects equine genes in an humanoid. This genetrainer gives the tireless health state, making the subject need less rest.  Genetrainers are implants that do not take the place of any given organ. Only one can be "installed" at a time. Using a second genetrainer will have no effect. Bear in mind that a genetrainer modifies the genes of the human subject, and only death will get rid of its effects.

The most majestic of horses is proud and magnificent, and doesnt care for your rules, man. So keep them properly penned up, because theyll try to escape to freedom so they can run wild and free. And then wonder where all the carrots, sugar cubes and salt licks have disappeared to.  A perfect equine animal, paragon of all similar animals with no needless junk genetic data. Besides the various improvements to the baseline animals abilities, this paragon makes for an excellent mount and pack animal for caravans.

items.armor: Armor - Blunt: 40%, Armor - Sharp: 40%, Armor - Heat: 75%
items.description: A helmet designed to keep the occupant alive in outer space. Recycles oxygen and provides resistance to toxic airborne particulates.

items.armor: Armor - Blunt: 40%, Armor - Sharp: 40%, Armor - Heat: 75%
items.description: A suit designed to keep the occupant alive in outer space. Includes small thrusters for movement.
Particles whose behavior defies conventionally-understood physics, safely contained. Can be used to construct a wide range of devices.

The FAMAS (Fusil d'Assaut de la Manufacture d'Armes de Saint-tienne, in English "Assault Rifle from the Saint-tienne Weapon Factory") is a bullpup-styled assault rifle designed and manufactured in France by MAS located in Saint-tienne, which is now a member of the French government-owned Nexter group.    It was later replaced as the service rifle of the French military by the HK416F.

The karabinek szturmowy wzr 1996 Beryl (English: assault carbine model 1996 beryllium) is a Polish 5.56mm assault rifle, designed and produced by the ucznik Arms Factory in the city of Radom.    The rifle is to replace the 7.6239mm AKM and 5.4539mm FB Tantal used in the Polish Armed Forces.
Chickenbear feathers can be gathered and processed into a fine powder, which produces a mild euphoric sensation when burned and inhaled. Featherdust use can produce a dependency.

A payload of feline genetic material. Can be used at the genomorpher to create a growth cell of a hybrid animal. This tier 1 genome can be used as either a primary or secondary genome.  <color=#E5E54C>Gameplay effect:</color> All feline hybrids have an inherent dodge chance. Combat feline hybrids get a further increase to dodge chance.  <color=#E5E54C>Extraction:</color> Can be extracted via the genome extractor table or any genome excavator from:

Directly injects feline genes in an humanoid. This genetrainer gives the keen sight health state, increasing shooting accuracy.  Genetrainers are implants that do not take the place of any given organ. Only one can be "installed" at a time. Using a second genetrainer will have no effect. Bear in mind that a genetrainer modifies the genes of the human subject, and only death will get rid of its effects.

An incredible, large fur baby that not only wants you to scratch its belly, but regularly and without fear of getting your eyes gouged out by their massive claws. Also theyre smart enough to go after prey less than half their size, but thats more so they dont have to spend so much time grooming themselves afterwards.  A perfect feline animal, paragon of all similar animals with no needless junk genetic data. Besides the various improvements to the baseline animals abilities, this paragon is incredibly intelligent and can be properly trained with minimal retraining, as well as being an excellent and affectionate companion.  <color=#E5E54C>Gameplay effect:</color> Like all cat hybrids, they have an improved melee dodge ability and a short nuzzle period. Cat reflexes ability: twice per day, it can use an ability that gives it further melee capabilities.

An axe (sometimes ax in American English; see spelling differences) is an implement that has been used for millennia to shape, split and cut wood, to harvest timber, as a weapon, and as a ceremonial or heraldic symbol. The axe has many forms and specialised uses but generally consists of an axe head with a handle, or helve.  This variant of axe is the Felling Axe.

Compressed medicine that allows hybrids to develop functional sexual organs. Effectively allows hybrids to reproduce with the exact same species.  Note: Insectoid hybrids are always incapable of reproducing.

The FGM-148 Javelin is an American man-portable fire-and-forget anti-tank missile fielded to replace the M47 Dragon anti-tank missile in US service. (One-time use only, this version of Javelin has to be disposed of after one use.)     It uses an automatic infrared guidance that allows the user to seek cover immediately after launch, as opposed to wired-guided systems. The Javelin's HEAT warhead is capable of defeating modern tanks by attacking them from above, and is also useful against fortifications in a direct attack flight.
A sweet fruit that grows on trees.
A complex bake assembled with care from a wide selection of ingredients and flour.
A complex dessert assembled with care from a wide selection of ingredients.
A complex grilled meat assembled with care from a wide selection of ingredients. Very filling, grilled meats allow people to not feel hunger for a long time. Freezing them ruins this effect.
A complex soup assembled with care from a wide selection of ingredients.

An axe (sometimes ax in American English; see spelling differences) is an implement that has been used for millennia to shape, split and cut wood, to harvest timber, as a weapon, and as a ceremonial or heraldic symbol. The axe has many forms and specialised uses but generally consists of an axe head with a handle, or helve.  This variant of axe is the Fire Axe.
A swarm of small, deadly flies. Almost impossible to hit using rudimentary weapons, the ideal way of dealing with fleshflies is by using fire, to which they are highly susceptible.

Something went terribly wrong. A huge and weird growth has spawned within the electrowomb, breaking it completely and spreading all around. This growth is a hatchery for small flies that can devour any living creature to the bone. It seems to be sensitive to daylight, but no one knows how far it can spread at night.

Something went terribly wrong. This wretched creature is struggling to keep breathing. Its rabid, and the moment it crawled out of the vat it started to look for the next unfortunate living being to destroy. It can and should be slain as soon as possible, as each additional kill only prolongs its life.

Something went terribly wrong. This wretched creature is struggling to keep breathing. Whilst it doesnt pose any real threat and it seems quite friendly, it requires a tremendous amount of love and attention for it to find the strength to live another day.
Simple flour, used in baking.
A drug for blocking flu. Works on animals. Take every five days.   Makes 2.

The FN F2000 is a 5.56x45mm NATO bullpup assault rifle, designed by FN Herstal in Belgium. The F2000 made its debut in March 2001 at the IDEX defence exhibition held in Abu Dhabi, in the United Arab Emirates.

The FAL (French: Fusil Automatique Lger, English: Light Automatic Rifle) is a battle rifle designed by Belgian small arms designers Dieudonn Saive and Ernest Vervier and manufactured by FN Herstal.  During the Cold War the FAL was adopted by many countries of the North Atlantic Treaty Organization (NATO), with the notable exception of the United States. It is one of the most widely used rifles in history, having been used by more than 90 countries. Because of its prevalence and widespread usage among the militaries of many NATO and first world countries during the Cold War it was given the title "The right arm of the Free World".

The FAL (French: Fusil Automatique Lger, English: Light Automatic Rifle) is a battle rifle designed by Belgian small arms designers Dieudonn Saive and Ernest Vervier and manufactured by FN Herstal.  During the Cold War the FAL was adopted by many countries of the North Atlantic Treaty Organization (NATO), with the notable exception of the United States. It is one of the most widely used rifles in history, having been used by more than 90 countries. Because of its prevalence and widespread usage among the militaries of many NATO and first world countries during the Cold War it was given the title "The right arm of the Free World".

The FN Five-seven, trademarked as the Five-seven, is a semi-automatic pistol designed and manufactured by FN Herstal in Belgium. The pistol is named for its 5.7-mm (.224 in) bullet diameter, and the trademark capitalization style is intended to emphasize the manufacturer's initialsFN.

The FN Five-seven, trademarked as the Five-seven, is a semi-automatic pistol designed and manufactured by FN Herstal in Belgium. The pistol is named for its 5.7-mm (.224 in) bullet diameter, and the trademark capitalization style is intended to emphasize the manufacturer's initialsFN.

The FN MAG is a Belgian 7.62 mm general-purpose machine gun, designed in the early 1950s at Fabrique Nationale (FN) by Ernest Vervier. It has been used by more than 80 countries, and it has been made under licence in several countries, including Argentina, Canada (as the C6 GPMG), Egypt, India and the United Kingdom.

The FN P90, also known as the FN Project 1990, is a personal defense weapon (PDW) designed and manufactured by FN Herstal in Belgium. Created in response to NATO requests for a replacement for 919mm Parabellum firearms, the P90 was designed as a compact but powerful firearm for vehicle crews, operators of crew-served weapons, support personnel, special forces, and counter-terrorist groups.

The FN P90, also known as the FN Project 1990, is a personal defense weapon (PDW) designed and manufactured by FN Herstal in Belgium. Created in response to NATO requests for a replacement for 919mm Parabellum firearms, the P90 was designed as a compact but powerful firearm for vehicle crews, operators of crew-served weapons, support personnel, special forces, and counter-terrorist groups.
A mini-granary for storing raw food and plant matter.
An electric canning stove, food press, and prep table.

A 2x2 shelf for storing perishable items. 4 layer shelf. Allowing up to 4x items per gound square. Items stored in this will not affect room beauty and they won't deteriorate, even if outside.     This storage area is set to Important and has by default all the items that spoil from vanilla and the garden mods.   Things to store here: Foods, Drugs, Medicines, Plant Matters, and Animals Corpses.
A drink made from pressing fruit for their juice.   Drink Effects: Consciousness and Blood Filtration.
A slice of pie.   Food Effects: Well Fed: Baked Good.    Increased Consciousness and Metabolism
An un-powered version of the canning stove, food press, and prep table. Makes simple items. Requires 40% work to make items here.
Makes sweet treats.

The civilian MR308 was used to develop the G28, a designated marksman rifle for the German Bundeswehr (Federal Army) deployment to the War in Afghanistan.    The semi-automatic G28 is chambered for 7.6251mm NATO and has a factory warrantied accuracy of 45 mm dispersion at 100 meters (0.45 mil or 1.5 moa) when fired with 10 rounds using OTM/HPBT/Sierra Match King ammunition.

The G36 is a 5.5645mm assault rifle, designed in the early 1990s by Heckler anf Koch in Germany as a replacement for the heavier 7.62mm G3 battle rifle.   It was accepted into service with the Bundeswehr in 1997, replacing the G3.

The G3 (Gewehr 3) is a 7.6251mm NATO, select-fire battle rifle developed in the 1950s by the German armament manufacturer Heckler and Koch (HK) in collaboration with the Spanish state-owned design and development agency CETME (Centro de Estudios Tcnicos de Materiales Especiales).  The G3 was the service rifle of the armed forces of Germany until it was replaced by the G36 in the 1990s.
A cup of coffee
Fresh water small fish. Normally caught in shallow waters.
A drink made from brew tea leaves.
Produces 2000 heating units for radiators and hot water tanks. Requires chemfuel for fuel. Can be controlled by thermostats.

A fertility booster that also forces the produced embryo to develop female characteristics. Effectively allows hybrids to reproduce with the exact same species.  Note: Insectoid hybrids are always incapable of reproducing.

A fertility booster that also forces the produced embryo to develop male characteristics. Effectively allows hybrids to reproduce with the exact same species.  Note: Insectoid hybrids are always incapable of reproducing.

An advanced and specialized workbench capable of manufacturing medical-grade implants and mixing genetic boosters specifically tuned to Genomorphers. These include but arent limited to boosters that improve the safety or stability of hybrids and even micro-controllers that enable direct user-input.
