The Genetrainer bench allows jury rigging of mech serum neurotrainers, psytrainers, healers and resurrectors to craft genetrainers, single use artifacts that inject animal genetic material in a human being, acting as a powerful implant that doesn't take the place of any organ in the body.

A stable genetic material consumed by the genomorpher machine that serves as a framework for hybrid experimentation. After the framework is used to create a growthcell, the genoframe is empty and discarded.  Awful genoframe will result in a hybrid with greatly decreased stats over a normal hybrid.

A stable genetic material consumed by the genomorpher machine that serves as a framework for hybrid experimentation. After the framework is used to create a growthcell, the genoframe is empty and discarded.  Excellent genoframe will result in a hybrid with significantly improved stats over a normal hybrid.

A stable genetic material consumed by the genomorpher machine that serves as a framework for hybrid experimentation. After the framework is used to create a growthcell, the genoframe is empty and discarded.  Good genoframe will result in a hybrid with slightly improved stats over a normal hybrid.

A stable genetic material consumed by the genomorpher machine that serves as a framework for hybrid experimentation. After the framework is used to create a growthcell, the genoframe is empty and discarded.  Legendary genoframe will result in an incredibly powerful hybrid thats eclipsing normal creatures.

A stable genetic material consumed by the genomorpher machine that serves as a framework for hybrid experimentation. After the framework is used to create a growthcell, the genoframe is empty and discarded.  Masterwork genoframe will result in a hybrid with superior stats over a normal hybrid.

A stable genetic material consumed by the genomorpher machine that serves as a framework for hybrid experimentation. After the framework is used to create a growthcell, the genoframe is empty and discarded.  Normal genoframe will result in a hybrid with baseline stats.

A stable genetic material consumed by the genomorpher machine that serves as a framework for hybrid experimentation. After the framework is used to create a growthcell, the genoframe is empty and discarded.  Poor genoframe will result in a hybrid with slightly decreased stats over a normal hybrid.

A simplified genome extraction device designed to be usable by even the most simple-minded goon, as such it resembles a caulking gun that works in reverse. The best genetic material can be found in the brain and the automated, single-use design instantly compresses this material into a usable genome.  The desired subject needs to be docile and trusting of the user who intends on scooping out their brain in a process that is not-quite instantaneous. It is recommended to anesthetize the creature as any sudden movement on their part will interrupt the whole process. Alternatively, it will also work on a dead body...  <color=#E5E54C>Gameplay effect:</color> This excavator can be used to acquire the following genomes:

A specialized extraction module that is equipped to extract the genomes from a subjects corpse. The material is converted into a soupish-mixture which is then condensed into the relevant genome. Processing speed is influenced by intelligence, as it relies on knowing which button to press, when to press it and where to find it under the intimidating number of submenus.  <color=#E5E54C>Gameplay effect:</color> The genome extractor table will only work for tier 1 genomes. For tier 2 (insectoids, reptiles, equines) and tier 3 (colossals) you will need genome excavators, built on the genetics tinkering table or found on abandoned labs.

A specialized extraction module that is equipped to extract the genomes from a subjects corpse. The material is converted into a soupish-mixture which is then condensed into an extremely complex genome. Completely useless by itself, but functions as a template which can be compared to another genome. The procedure removes any excess genetic information and renders them completely identical.  Bear in mind that this machine cannot duplicate some genomes, such as colossal.

A machine where the miracle - or horror - of birth happens using automated procedures, a little genetic hand-waving and a great heaping dose of lost sleep. The inserted Genoframe is influenced by two genomes, one dominant and one recessive, and can be modified with optional boosters.  The process isnt perfect, due to material contamination, missing chromosomes or simple bad luck, and can result in something completely unwanted being developed. For the machine, it makes no difference whether its trying to grow an animal or a comically large fruit. The resulting growth cell has a limited lifespan as the embryonic fluid will start breaking down if not allowed to gestate properly.  <color=#E5E54C>Gameplay notes:</color> If the process to deliver ingredients to the genomorpher is interrupted, the ingredients that have already been inserted in it will deteriorate and be lost.

A power glitterworld drug for preventing most infections before they take hold.   Blocks malaria, sleeping sickness, plague, infections, gut worms, muscle parasites, flu, fibrous and sensory mechanites. Must be taken every 15 days to remain effective.  This drug only prevents new infections. It does not cure existing infections - even those that are not yet discovered.
A synthetic precursor chemical. While it is useless on its own, many drugs require glitterworld neutroamine as an ingredient.

The Glock pistol is a series of polymer-framed, short recoil-operated, locked-breech semi-automatic pistols designed and produced by Austrian Glock Ges.m.b.H.. It entered Austrian military and police service by 1982 after it was the top performer in reliability and safety tests.   Glocks are also popular firearms among civilians for recreational and competition shooting, home and self-defense, and concealed carry or open carry.

The Glock pistol is a series of polymer-framed, short recoil-operated, locked-breech semi-automatic pistols designed and produced by Austrian Glock Ges.m.b.H.. It entered Austrian military and police service by 1982 after it was the top performer in reliability and safety tests.   Glocks are also popular firearms among civilians for recreational and competition shooting, home and self-defense, and concealed carry or open carry.

The Glock pistol is a series of polymer-framed, short recoil-operated, locked-breech semi-automatic pistols designed and produced by Austrian Glock Ges.m.b.H.. It entered Austrian military and police service by 1982 after it was the top performer in reliability and safety tests.   Glocks are also popular firearms among civilians for recreational and competition shooting, home and self-defense, and concealed carry or open carry.

The Glock 34 is a competition version of the Glock 17. It is similar to its predecessor, the Glock 17L, but with a slightly shorter slide and barrel, to meet the maximum size requirements for many sanctioned action pistol sporting events.   The Glock 34 Combat Master has been beautifully tuned from the original version at Taran Tactical Innovations. This particular version was used by a legendary assassin known as "Baba Yaga".

The GOL-Sniper Magnum is a bolt-action sniper rifle designed by the German company Gol-Matic GmbH of Birkenau, Hessen. The rifle is available in tactical as well as sporting and match configurations.    It is developed from Austrian Steyr SSG 69.
A sweet fruit that grows on vines.
A culinary work of art, characterized by refined, even elaborate preparation and presentation of an aesthetically balanced, albeit low quantity bake.
A culinary work of art, characterized by refined, even elaborate preparation and presentation of an aesthetically balanced, albeit low quantity dessert.

A culinary work of art, characterized by refined, even elaborate preparation and presentation of an aesthetically balanced, albeit low quantity grilled meat. Very filling, grilled meats allow people to not feel hunger for a long time. Freezing them ruins this effect.
A culinary work of art, characterized by refined, even elaborate preparation and presentation of an aesthetically balanced, albeit low quantity meal.
A culinary work of art, characterized by refined, even elaborate preparation and presentation of an aesthetically balanced, albeit low quantity soup.

Hard apples, with a light green skin and crisp, juicy flesh. The flavour is tart and acidic. It remains firm when baked, making it a very popular cooking apple used in pies, where it can be sweetened.
A sweet fruit that grows on vines.
A grill is a device that cooks food by applying heat from below. This is a wood fired grill that needs wood as fuel to work.
Two slices of bread grilled with cheese melt in the middle.   Food Effects: BloodPumping.
Meats and Vegetables skewered on a stick and grilled to perfection.   Food Effects: Metabolism and Manipulation.
A loaf of Potenta that has been sliced and grilled to perfection.   Food Effects: Manipulation and Metabolism.
Meat that has been cooked over a grill.
Vegetables that have been cooked over a grill.

Yellow, elongated berries. These bananas have been genetically modified to resist the fungal infections that nearly caused their extinction in old Terra. The Gros Michel variety has a distinct taste, different from that of Cavendish variety bananas.

A portable, human-made casing designed to hold an embryo until it is transferred to a relevant Electrowomb, similar to fertilized eggs that require incubation. The embryonic fluid is unstable due to the unnatural genetic combination, so it will need to be implanted within 7 days after its creation. This growth cell has to be kept at a temperature between 0 and 50 degrees Celsius.
Why? Why, why, why, WHY? Cheese. With hair. WHY???
This milk seems to be filled with strands of grey wool. Disgusting, and quite hard to drink...
This is a set of hampers made out of fabric.  The various pockets allow storing large amounts of diverse small items with ease.  If you really want to store fabric in bags, see the mod settings!

An axe (sometimes ax in American English; see spelling differences) is an implement that has been used for millennia to shape, split and cut wood, to harvest timber, as a weapon, and as a ceremonial or heraldic symbol. The axe has many forms and specialised uses but generally consists of an axe head with a handle, or helve.  This variant of axe is the Roughneck Hand Axe.
A hard candy made from sugar and fruit juice.   Food Effects: Moving.
A simple type of biscuit. Tastes bland, but not offensive. Made from grains. It lasts a very long time without refrigeration. Great for travelling.
Capsules containing genetic stabilizers that help maintain the dominant-recessive genome relationship. Effectively reduces the chance of the hybrid having the opposite intended result.

"A hayloft is a space above a barn, stable or cow-shed, traditionally used for storage of hay or other fodder for the animals below. Haylofts were used mainly before the widespread use of industrial sized farm machinery allowed creating very large haybales that cannot be easily lifted for storing..."  --Encyclopedia Galactica  Let's be honest here.  Unless you're using some farming mods I don't know about, your colonists are probably making piles of hay by hand, which is slow, backbreaking labor.  You know what?  Most farming is slow, backbreaking labor, and your colonists can't even hire migrant workers from other colonies.  Treat farmers and farm workers with respect: they work a lot harder than YOU do ;) Amazing people, good food.  This structure can be used to store hay, silage, and various other plant materials off of damp floors.  You probably want to build it under a (very tall) roof.

A dose of semi-coherent mechanites designed to rapidly heal injuries within the host.  They're so powerful they can regenerate scars, missing organs and lost limbs.  Due to how mechanites work only one strain can exist harmoniously inside the hosts body.  However, it is possible to remove a mechanite strain with surgery.
large metal parts such as cylinders, cranks, manifolds and turbine blades that cannot be simply processed by smithing.
an six cylender distel engine with powerful torque, it is commonly used by heavy vehicles and ships.

items.armor: Armor - Sharp: 106%, Armor - Blunt: 45%, Armor - Heat: 54%
items.description: A pressure-sealed power armor helmet, designed to keep the occupant alive in outer space. Recycles oxygen and provides resistance to toxic airborne particulates.

items.armor: Armor - Blunt: 45%, Armor - Sharp: 108%, Armor - Heat: 75%
items.description: A pressure-sealed suit of powered armor, designed to keep the occupant alive in outer space. Includes small thrusters for movement.
A relatively flat circular pad where droids can hunker down and go into hibernation mode.
A torpedo tipped with high explosives. Can be fired from torpedo tubes. Explodes when damaged.
A living piece of an insect hive. Used to make a hydro-jelly farm to produce insect jelly. Eww I think it's still moving...

The Heckler and Koch HK416 is an assault rifle designed and manufactured by Heckler and Koch. Although its design is in large part based on the AR-15 class of weapons, specifically the Colt M4 carbine family issued to the U.S. military, it uses an HK-proprietary short-stroke gas piston system originally derived from the ArmaLite AR-18 (the same system was also used in Heckler and Koch's earlier G36 family of rifles).   It was the standard assault rifle of the French Armed Forces and Norwegian Armed Forces, and was the weapon used by SEAL Team Six to kill Osama Bin Laden in 2011.

The HK69A1 is a 40 mm grenade launcher developed and produced by the German arms manufacturer Heckler and Koch (HK). The weapon was designed to engage enemy troops and strongpoints out to a distance of 350 m; it can also be used to deploy smoke grenades and illumination flares.
Super sweet, super delicious, honey is used as a natural sweetener in all sorts of goodies.  Also used in the production of mead. Doesn't spoil, though can deteriorate if left outside.
Mead can taste good, but its main effect is intoxication. Excessive consumption can lead to alcohol blackouts and, over time, addiction.

A potent, spicy sauce made from blending and simmering chilis and other spices. While particularly strong hot sauces hurt at first, they are known to numb pain and work up a warm sweat shortly after consumption.
This enormous bear pelt is probably valuable as a trade good. Or it can also be repurposed as a huge rug.
A bear pelt rug. Taxidermy seems to be in vogue on the Rim!
A bearcat pelt rug. This thing seems to be quite more exotic than other pelt rugs!

A canister of compressed ceramo-metallic foam. When sprayed, it rapidly hardens into an airtight and relatively durable barrier. Its primary use involves patching destroyed sections of starship hull until proper repairs can be made.
An improvement over the bionic Power Claw, these claws have been vat-grown with a mixture of human and bear DNA, and replace the subject's hand with versatile, non-retractable claws.
Grafts of bear muscle tissue on the subject's torso increase overall strength and stamina. These grafts however tend to stimulate the production of an abundance of body hair.
These skin nodules can be integrated in a human's torso, causing a huge explosion if the subjects dies violently.
This huge leporid ear gives amazing enhanced hearing. Also, super kawaii!
This hybrid humanoid / feline eye provides improved night vision, at the expense of a certain short-sightedness outside and during the day. Ideal for nyctophile colonists.
A reinforced bionic heart that acts like a miniature 4-stroke internal combustion engine powered by chemfuel to pump blood through the body.
A reinforced bionic stomach that uses a combination of gastric acid and chemfuel to efficiently digest food.

This hybrid humanoid / insectoid eye provides improved vision in a wide range of different wavelengths, including those usually outside the human range, completely modifying the way the subject perceives their surroundings.
A set of improved teeth designed to rapidly chew and ingest any kind of food. Leaves kind of a mess, though...
Grotesque but powerful hand blades that have been modified to be used in mining operations, increasing both speed and yield.
A biochip that modifies the brain to reduce the need for sleep.

A synthetic skin substitute that is much thicker and a much better insulator than human skin. This provides a measure of defense but, more importantly, makes the subject more resistant to high temperatures.

These hybrid humanoid / insectoid feeling appendages can be implanted in a subject's head, completely modifying the way the subject "sees" and feels the surrounding world. The experience may be slightly overwhelming due to sensorial overload.
This is a bioelectronic kidney prosthesis that greatly improves the efficiency of the subject's kidney by using insectoid tissue, providing resistance to toxic substances.
A biochip that reduces pain sensitivity, allowing the subject to survive pain shock.
A bionic vomeronasal organ that allows the subject pheromonal communication with other animals, increasing the chance of taming and training them successfully.
By implanting muffalo mammaries into a colonist... Wait, what??? Who came up with this idea????? Anyway... this implant allows your colonist to be milked... What the...

A synthetic skin substitute that is much thicker and a much better insulator than human skin. This provides a measure of defense but, more importantly, makes the subject more resistant to low temperatures.
By weaving muffalo muscle strands with the subjects muscular system, strength, resilience and carrying capacity are greatly increased.
A biochip using animal stem cells to reinforce the natural abilities of human neurons, increasing learning and research speed.

You know you have gone too far in your scientific experiments when you are implanting a human being with an ovipositor. This will enable the colonist to lay chicken eggs twice a day. It hurts as hell, though. Also, yuck.
Artificial hearing aids that block psychic emanations, providing considerable resistance to mechanoids' psychic attacks.
A genetically modified thrumbo horn that can be implanted in a subject's forehead. Nasty.
A synthetic skin substitute that is much thicker and a much better insulator than human skin. This provides a lot of defense and makes the subject more resistant to extremes of temperature.
This hybrid implant substitutes the subject's jaw with a set of venomous fangs. Useful in combat, but not very comfortable.
The subjects legs can be modified by weaving hybrid human/wolf muscle fibers within the base tissue, giving them a significant strength and speed boost.

A payload of humanoid genetic material. Can be used at the genomorpher to create a growth cell of a hybrid animal. This tier 1 genome can be used as either a primary or secondary genome.  <color=#E5E54C>Gameplay effect:</color> All humanoid hybrids have a somewhat decent level of intelligence and can do various tasks around the colony.  <color=#E5E54C>Extraction:</color> Can be extracted via the genome extractor table or any genome excavator from any sentient humanoid.

There is a saying that all of life is a circle, and that eventually everything returns to its origins only to begin again. This particular humanoid has undergone some mental evolution while at the same time suffering from physical devolution, resembling more closely humanitys distant evolutionary ancestors. Just dont say monkey.  A perfect humanoid animal, paragon of all similar animals with no needless junk genetic data. Besides the various improvements to the baseline animals abilities, this paragon can drive mans curiosity ever forward by providing a boost to research speed with a well-placed insightful word of wisdom.  <color=#E5E54C>Gameplay effect:</color> Humanoid paragons will periodically engage other colonists in conversation, talking about a variety of topics. This increases the social recreation needs of those they interact with by 10% (subject to diminishing returns like all joy types). If using Ideology, humanoid hybrids are subject to precepts. Research drive ability: offers investigative insights to nearby researches, allowing them to more easily reach a breakthrough by increasing research speed by 10%.

An extremely cursed riding companion that can vocally explain in excruciating detail the troubles it goes through as a beast of burden. Most people dont like to be reminded that animals are capable of feeling, especially if they can vocalise themselves in human speech. Dont be surprised if no one wants to eat or wear butchered parts of this creature, as it looks like a misshapen human with cloven hands.  An equine hybrid with recessive humanoid genes. Very intelligent and relatively low maintenance, they make for a decent rideable pack animal. Their main advantage comes in their ability to cheer up the travellers in a caravan, however it doesnt understand social cues and can throw out some devastating social commentary.  <color=#E5E54C>Gameplay effect:</color> All equine hybrids are good for caravaning. A caravan with one of them needs a shorter resting period, only stopping to rest between 23:30 PM and 4 AM. Humanoid hybrids will periodically engage other colonists in conversation, talking about a variety of topics. This increases the social recreation needs of those they interact with by 10% (subject to diminishing returns like all joy types). The hurseman engages caravan members too while caravaning, causing mood boosts (up to +15). 10% of the time however it will insult them, making them loose mood (up to -30). If using Ideology, humanoid hybrids are subject to precepts.
Overlapping plates of hardened chitin. Really durable in combat, but provides little protection from weather.
Light, pliable sheets of scaly skin. Light, strong, and insulates well.
Fabric spun from silk fibers. Resists blunt and sharp damage easily, but provides almost no protection against extreme heat.
A drug for blocking pain. Take every day.

An ice axe is a multi-purpose hiking and climbing tool used by mountaineers in both the ascent and descent of routes that involve frozen conditions with snow or ice. An ice axe can be held and employed in a number of different ways, depending on the terrain encountered. In its simplest role, the ice axe is used like a walking stick in the uphill hand, the mountaineer holding the head in the center.  This variant is the DMM Fly ice axe.
A sweet frozen treat made from milk.   Food Effects: Moving and Blood Pumping.

A small durable core of archotech design said to make its host immortal through rapid regeneration.  Its inner workings are a complete mystery, its unclear how it can endlessly regenerate a person seemingly from nothing.  Once implanted the core cannot be removed without damaging the device rendering it inert.

A dose of semi-coherent mechanites which travel throughout the body in order to fight off diseases within the host.  While mechanite strains normally conflict with one another this one is designed to remain in sleep mode the majority of the time and only awaken temporarily to deal with threats to the hosts health.  As such its able to coexist with other more aggressive mechanite strains.  Unfortunately, this has the downside of the mechanites being unable to remain active long to fight off existing conditions that have had time to take hold in the hosts system.
Capsules containing genetic restorative medicine that helps prevent genomes from breaking down prematurely. Effectively helps mitigate the possibility of the hybrid ending in complete failure.

This particular machine can be explained as a simplified and miniaturized version of a Genomorpher, using only a single genome which influences an inserted Genoframe. Instead of trying to create an entire animal, it instead creates very specific limbs or organs. Due to the vastly simplified process and minimal variables, no complications arise during the process and the resulting product is similarly influenced by the quality of the Genoframe.  The Implant Augmentator can be used to create implants for animals - not just hybrids - with the quality of Genoframe dictating the deficits or bonuses those implants provide. Not all implants are created equal, some being inferior replacements and others providing new capabilities provided the animal in question can support them. Human implants are also a possibility.
Self-assembling machinery that fuses with the specimens nerve centers during the growth process. Effectively allows hybrids to be drafted.  This booster can't be crafted, only scavenged.

Self-assembling machinery that fuses with the specimens nerve centers during the growth process. Allows hybrids to be drafted and causes sharp plasteel claws to grow from one of the creature's limbs.  This booster can't be crafted, only scavenged.

Self-assembling machinery that fuses with the specimens nerve centers during the growth process. Allows hybrids to be drafted and creates a strong mechanite skin that protects the animal from harm.  This booster can't be crafted, only scavenged.

A fertility booster that also forces the produced embryo to develop female characteristics. Effectively allows hybrids to reproduce with the exact same species.  This booster can't be crafted, only scavenged.  Note: Insectoid hybrids are always incapable of reproducing.

A fertility booster that also forces the produced embryo to develop male characteristics. Effectively allows hybrids to reproduce with the exact same species.  This booster can't be crafted, only scavenged.  Note: Insectoid hybrids are always incapable of reproducing.

Capsules containing genetic stabilizers that help maintain the dominant-recessive genome relationship. Greatly reduces the chance of the hybrid having the opposite intended result, at the expense of more processing time.  This booster can't be crafted, only scavenged.

Capsules containing genetic restorative medicine that helps prevent genomes from breaking down prematurely. Greatly helps mitigate the possibility of the hybrid ending in complete failure, at the expense of more processing time.  This booster can't be crafted, only scavenged.
Insect jelly cut with sweetener then sealed as a preserve. Very rich and sweet, while being surprisingly healthy.

A payload of insectoid genetic material. Can be used at the genomorpher to create a growth cell of a hybrid animal. This tier 2 genome can only be used as primary genome.  <color=#E5E54C>Gameplay effect:</color> All hybrids with insectoid genome get 100% toxic resistance as well as an armor increase. Combat hybrids get a further increase to armor.  <color=#E5E54C>Extraction:</color> Can only be extracted via any genome excavator from:

Directly injects insectoid genes in an humanoid. This genetrainer gives the eusocial mind health state, making the subject specialized in construction and repair at the expense of plant and animal skills.  Genetrainers are implants that do not take the place of any given organ. Only one can be "installed" at a time. Using a second genetrainer will have no effect. Bear in mind that a genetrainer modifies the genes of the human subject, and only death will get rid of its effects.

A terrifying callback to the original Sorne geneline, this mobile hive was originally designed to engage the mechanoid enemy head-on. By carrying an entire colony of insects with hardened mandibles, their ability to practically disassemble the mechanical menace proved just as effective at turning against their human overlords.  A perfect insectoid animal, paragon of all similar animals with no needless junk genetic data. Besides the various improvements to the baseline animals abilities, this paragon is extremely intelligent and carries a dangerous brood of warrior flies. A burst of pheromones summons the drones to protect their hive and queen, shredding apart all other nearby creatures.  <color=#E5E54C>Gameplay effect:</color> All insectoid hybrids have good armor and no toxic sensitivity, but they are always sterile and can't reproduce, even if a fertility booster is used to create them. Insect clouds ability: twice a day it can create insect clouds around it that damage any animal crossing them, except insectoid paragons, which are immune.
Ironwood is stronger and more beautiful then normal wood. Useful for building structures, weapons, and even simple prosthetics. Very beautiful decorative material.

A double-barreled shotgun is a break-action shotgun with two parallel barrels, allowing two single shots to be fired in quick succession. The IZh-43 (-43) is a Soviet and Russian double-barreled shotgun. IZh-43 was designed in early 1980s, in 1986 first shotguns were made. In January 2004, a contract was signed between the Remington Arms company and the Izhevsk Mechanical Plant. Russian firearms was bought by Remington and sold in USA (IZh-43 was sold as Remington Spartan 220 and IZh-43-1S was sold as Remington Spartan 210).

The Karabiner 98 kurz (Often abbreviated Kar98k or K98k and often incorrectly referred to as a K98) is a bolt-action rifle chambered for the 7.9257mm Mauser cartridge that was adopted on 21 June 1935 as the standard service rifle by the German Wehrmacht.   It was one of the final developments in the long line of Mauser military rifles. Although supplemented by semi- and fully automatic rifles during World War II, it remained the primary German service rifle until the end of the war in 1945.

The karambit or kerambit (as used in Indonesian), kurambik or karambiak (both from the Minangkabau language) is a small Indonesian curved knife resembling a claw from Minangkabau people of West Sumatra.  This karambit knife is of the Cold Steel Tiger variant.

A katana is a Japanese sword characterized by a curved, single-edged blade with a circular or squared guard and long grip to accommodate two hands. Developed later than the tachi, it was used by samurai in feudal Japan and worn with the blade facing upward. Since the Muromachi period, many old tachi were cut from the root and shortened, and the blade at the root was crushed and converted into katana.  This version is the Fudoshin custom made katana.

A katana is a Japanese sword characterized by a curved, single-edged blade with a circular or squared guard and long grip to accommodate two hands. Developed later than the tachi, it was used by samurai in feudal Japan and worn with the blade facing upward. Since the Muromachi period, many old tachi were cut from the root and shortened, and the blade at the root was crushed and converted into katana.  This version is a custom made, legendary Hattori Hanzo style katana.

A katana is a Japanese sword characterized by a curved, single-edged blade with a circular or squared guard and long grip to accommodate two hands. Developed later than the tachi, it was used by samurai in feudal Japan and worn with the blade facing upward. Since the Muromachi period, many old tachi were cut from the root and shortened, and the blade at the root was crushed and converted into katana.  This version is the Cold Steel Mizutori.
A thick sauce made from stewing tomatoes, both salty and tangy in tandem with a sweet aftertaste. Perfect for meaty meals or fried foods.

The KRISS Vector series are a family of weapons based upon the parent submachine gun design developed by KRISS USA. They use an unconventional delayed blowback system combined with in-line design to reduce perceived recoil and muzzle climb.

The Ksp 58 (Swedish: Kulspruta 58) is a Swedish variant of the Belgian FN MAG general purpose machine gun that is currently being manufactured by the Swedish company Carl Gustafs Stads Gevrsfaktori and was adopted by the Swedish Armed Forces in 1958. After 1945, many countries are trying to produce their own machine guns based on the MG 42 design. In the early 1950s, Belgian arms manufacturer FN Herstal succeeded in developing a general-purpose machine gun called the MAG. The initial Ksp 58A version used by Sweden was chambered for 6.555mm, while the B and later models were chambered for 7.6251mm NATO.

The L129A1 Sharpshooter is a marksman's rifle that has been fielded by UK forces since late 2010.  The weapon was procured in order to fill a capability gap identified by experience in Afghanistan, where British infantry units were often engaged by small arms fire from outside the range of their own assault rifles and light machine guns.

The Accuracy International Arctic Warfare rifle is a bolt-action sniper rifle designed and manufactured by the British company Accuracy International.    It has proved popular as a civilian, police, and military rifle since its introduction in the 1980s. The rifles have some features that improve performance in very cold conditions, without impairing operation in less extreme conditions.
A doormat to clean your feet.
A doormat to clean your feet.
A doormat to clean your feet.
A doormat to clean your feet.
A doormat to clean your feet.
A doormat to clean your feet.
A doormat to clean your feet.

A larger machine designed to simulate the environment of a mothers womb. Once a Growthcell has been inserted, the embryo can start growing all the way to its adult life stage before being released. Provides more growing room for larger specimens.
Three times the output of a standard radiator. Useful for larger rooms. Requires 300 heating units.
A masterpiece of the culinary arts, this bake nourishes the body, mind, and soul.
A masterpiece of the culinary arts, this dessert nourishes the body, mind, and soul.
A masterpiece of the culinary arts, this grilled meat nourishes the body, mind, and soul. Very filling, grilled meats allow people to not feel hunger for a long time. Freezing them ruins this effect.
A masterpiece of the culinary arts, this soup nourishes the body, mind, and soul.

The LeeEnfield is a bolt-action, magazine-fed, repeating rifle that served as the main firearm used by the military forces of the British Empire and Commonwealth during the first half of the 20th century.    It was the British Army's standard rifle from its official adoption in 1895 until 1957.
two-stroke cycle engine,it is simple and produce a large torque, but the fuel consumption is relatively higher.

It is doubtful that one would meet a crueller or more sadistic creature than this hybrid. It actively experiences joy when slaughtering tame animals and executing prisoners, the latter of which even provides a powerful boost which can be used before battle. Maybe it has something to do with taking pleasure in killing those that made it this way, but thats a story for another time.  A reptile hybrid with recessive humanoid genes. A very intelligent but combat-limited animal that performs surprisingly poorly against similar sized creatures. They will only passively engage creatures much smaller than itself and takes some twisted, psychotic pleasure in killing those who are completely helpless.  <color=#E5E54C>Gameplay effect:</color> Humanoid hybrids will periodically engage other colonists in conversation, talking about a variety of topics. This increases the social recreation needs of those they interact with by 10% (subject to diminishing returns like all joy types). If using Ideology, humanoid hybrids are subject to precepts. All reptile hybrids have good temperature tolerance ranges and venomous attacks. Lizardmen will obey order to slaughter other colony animals, as well as execute prisoners of the colony.
Produces 2000 heating units for piped radiators and hot water tanks. Heats the room and adjacent baths. Requires wood logs for fuel.

The Longbow 1S-1K (1 Shot - 1 Kill) is a MDC energy rail weapon which is constructed by the Maquis, using the reverse-engineer based on Chimeran technology circa 1950s in an alternate Earth invaded by creatures known as the "Chimera".
This lumpy cheese seems to have concentrated protein chunks, tasting like chicken nuggets. Colonists seem to like it.
This wool is extremely thick and warm. Probably the best wool in the animal kingdom.

The LVOA-C (manufactured by War Sport Industries by Inventor Joey Boswell) is a direct gas-impingement (DGI) operated rifle based on the AR-15. It features a proprietary barrel shroud with an integrated muzzle brake/flash suppressor which serves its intended manufacturing purpose to be a close quarter combat weapon with a low visibility operation application (LVOA). The assault rifle features both chamber options of 5.56X45mm NATO rounds and .223 Wylde.  The LVOA-C weighs 7 pounds (3.2 kg) unloaded (7.5 pounds (3.4 kg) with a 30-round magazine) and measures 35.5 inches (90 cm) in length (32.75 inches (83.2 cm) with a closed stock). It has been widely used by private military companies for overseas and domestic operations due to its reliability, low recoil and visual signature.

The Benelli M4 Super 90 is an Italian semi-automatic shotgun manufactured by Benelli Armi SpA.  On May 4, 1998, the United States Army's Armaments Research, Development and Engineering Center (ARDEC) at Picatinny Arsenal, New Jersey issued Solicitation #DAAE30-98-R-0401, requesting submissions for a new 12 gauge, semi-automatic combat shotgun for the U.S. military. In response to the request, Benelli Armi SpA of Urbino, Italy designed and built the Benelli M4 Super 90 Combat Shotgun. On August 4, 1998, five samples of the M4 were delivered to Aberdeen Proving Ground, Maryland, and after intense testing, the M4 had beaten the competition. In early 1999, ARDEC awarded the M1014 Joint Service Combat Shotgun contract to Heckler and Koch, American subsidiary for importation of the Benelli M4 Combat Shotgun. The first units (count of 20,000) were delivered to the United States Marine Corps in 1999. During testing, the prototype was named XM1014, but after adoption, the 'X' was dropped, and the weapon was officially designated the M1014.

The Benelli M4 Super 90 is an Italian semi-automatic shotgun manufactured by Benelli Armi SpA.  On May 4, 1998, the United States Army's Armaments Research, Development and Engineering Center (ARDEC) at Picatinny Arsenal, New Jersey issued Solicitation #DAAE30-98-R-0401, requesting submissions for a new 12 gauge, semi-automatic combat shotgun for the U.S. military.
