The M14 rifle, officially the United States Rifle, 7.62 mm, M14, is an American automatic rifle that fires 7.6251mm NATO (.308 in) ammunition.    It became the standard-issued rifle for the U.S. military in 1959 replacing the M1 Garand rifle in the U.S. Army by 1961 and the U.S. Marine Corps by 1965 until being replaced by the M16 rifle beginning in 1964.

The M16 rifle, officially designated Rifle, Caliber 5.56 mm, M16, is a United States military adaptation of the ArmaLite AR-15 rifle. The original M16 was a 5.56mm automatic rifle with a 20-round magazine.  In 1964, the M16 entered U.S. military service and the following year was deployed for jungle warfare operations during the Vietnam War. In 1969, the M16A1 replaced the M14 rifle to become the U.S. military's standard service rifle.

The M1911 also known as the Browning Pistol is a single-action, semi-automatic, magazine-fed, recoil-operated pistol chambered for the .45 ACP cartridge. It served as the standard-issue sidearm for the United States Armed Forces from 1911 to 1986. It was widely used in World War I, World War II, the Korean War, and the Vietnam War as well as the SovietAfghan War.

The M1911 also known as the Browning Pistol is a single-action, semi-automatic, magazine-fed, recoil-operated pistol chambered for the .45 ACP cartridge. It served as the standard-issue sidearm for the United States Armed Forces from 1911 to 1986. It was widely used in World War I, World War II, the Korean War, and the Vietnam War as well as the SovietAfghan War.

The CheyTac Intervention is an American bolt-action sniper rifle manufactured by CheyTac LLC, which can also be classified as an anti-materiel rifle. It is fed by a 7-round detachable single-stack magazine (an optional 5-round magazine is also available).    It is specifically chambered in either .408 Chey Tac or .375 Chey Tac ammunition.

The M24 Sniper Weapon System (SWS) is the military and police version of the Remington Model 700 rifle, M24 being the model name assigned by the United States Army after adoption as their standard sniper rifle in 1988.    The M24 is referred to as a "weapon system" because it consists of not only a rifle, but also a detachable telescopic sight and other accessories.

The M249 light machine gun (LMG), formerly designated the M249 Squad Automatic Weapon (SAW) and formally written as Light Machine Gun, 5.56 mm, M249, is the American adaptation of the Belgian FN Minimi, a light machine gun manufactured by the Belgian company FN Herstal (FN).

The M40 rifle is a bolt-action sniper rifle used by the United States Marine Corps. It has had four variantsthe M40, M40A1, M40A3, and M40A5.    The M40 was introduced in 1966. The changeover to the A1 model was completed in the 1970s, the A3 in the 2000s, and the A5 in 2009.

The M4 carbine is a shorter and lighter variant of the M16A2 assault rifle. The M4 is a 5.5645mm NATO, air-cooled, direct impingement gas-operated, magazine-fed carbine. It has a 14.5 in (370 mm) barrel and a telescoping stock.  The M4 carbine is extensively used by the United States Armed Forces and is largely replacing the M16 rifle in United States Army and United States Marine Corps combat units as the primary infantry weapon and service rifle.

The M4 carbine is a shorter and lighter variant of the M16A2 assault rifle. The M4 is a 5.5645mm NATO, air-cooled, direct impingement gas-operated, magazine-fed carbine. It has a 14.5 in (370 mm) barrel and a telescoping stock.  The M4 carbine is extensively used by the United States Armed Forces and is largely replacing the M16 rifle in United States Army and United States Marine Corps combat units as the primary infantry weapon and service rifle.

The M60, officially the United States Machine Gun, Caliber 7.62 mm, M60, is a family of American general-purpose machine guns firing 7.6251mm NATO cartridges from a disintegrating belt of M13 links. There are several types of ammunition approved for use in the M60, including ball, tracer, and armor-piercing rounds.

The Remington Model 700 is a series of bolt-action centerfire rifles manufactured by Remington Arms since 1962. It is a development of the Remington 721 and 722 series of rifles, which were introduced in 1948. The M24 and M40 military sniper rifles, used by the US Army and Marine Corps, respectively, are both based on the Model 700 design.    This version uses the Accuracy International Chassis System.

The M72 LAW (Light Anti-Tank Weapon), also referred to as the Light Anti-Armor Weapon or LAW as well as LAWS Light Anti-Armor Weapons System) is a portable one-shot 66-mm unguided anti-tank weapon. It is one-time use.

The M79 grenade launcher is a single-shot, shoulder-fired, break-action grenade launcher that fires a 4046mm grenade, which uses what the US Army calls the High-Low Propulsion System to keep recoil forces low, and first appeared during the Vietnam War. Because of its distinctive report, it has earned the nicknames of "Thumper", "Thump-Gun", "Bloop Tube", "Big Ed", "Elephant Gun," and "Blooper" among American soldiers as well as "Can Cannon" in reference to the grenade size; Australian units referred to it as the "Wombat Gun". The M79 can fire a wide variety of 40 mm rounds, including explosive, anti-personnel, smoke, buckshot, flechette (pointed steel projectiles with a vaned tail for stable flight), and illumination. While largely replaced by the M203, the M79 has remained in service in many units worldwide in niche roles.

The Barrett M82, standardized by the U.S. military as the M107, is a recoil-operated, semi-automatic anti-materiel sniper system developed by the American Barrett Firearms Manufacturing company. Despite its designation as an anti-materiel rifle, it is used by some armed forces as an anti-personnel system.    It is also called the Light Fifty for its .50 BMG (12.799mm NATO) chambering and significantly lighter weight compared to previous applications.

The M84 is the currently-issued stun grenade ("flashbang") of the United States Armed Forces and SWAT teams throughout the United States. Upon detonation, it emits an intensely loud "bang" of 170180 decibels and a blinding flash of more than one million candela within five feet of initiation, sufficient to cause immediate flash blindness, deafness, tinnitus, and inner ear disturbance.

The Beretta M9  officially the Pistol, Semiautomatic, 9mm, M9  is the designation for the Beretta 92FS semi-automatic pistol by the United States Armed Forces. The M9 was adopted by the United States military as their service pistol in 1985.  The M9 won a competition in the 1980s to replace the M1911A1 as the primary sidearm of the U.S. military, beating many other contenders, and only narrowly defeating the SIG P226 for cost reasons.

The Military Armament Corporation Model 10, officially abbreviated as "M10" or "M-10", and more commonly known as the MAC-10, is a compact, blowback operated machine pistol/submachine gun that was developed by Gordon B. Ingram in 1964. It is chambered in either .45 ACP or 9mm. A two-stage suppressor by Sionics was designed for the MAC-10, which not only abates the noise created, but makes it easier to control on full automatic (although it also makes the gun far less compact and concealable). For a decade, the semi-automatic pistol version of the weapon was forbidden in the U.S. under the assault weapons ban enacted by Congress in 1994.

A machete is a broad blade used either as an agricultural implement similar to an axe, or in combat like a long-bladed knife. The blade is typically 30 to 45 centimetres (12 to 18 in) long and usually under 3 millimetres (0.12 in) thick. In the Spanish language, the word is possibly a diminutive form of the word macho, which was used to refer to sledgehammers.  This variant is the Gerber Gator machete and helps with plant work speed and harvest yields.

The kukri (English: /kkri/) or khukuri (Nepali: , pronounced [kukuri]) is a type of machete originating from the Indian subcontinent, and is traditionally associated with the Nepali-speaking Gurkhas of Nepal and India. The knife has a distinct recurve in its blade. It serves multiple purposes as a melee weapon and also as a regular cutting tool throughout most of South Asia. The blade has traditionally served the role of a basic utility knife for the Gurkhas.

A machete is a broad blade used either as an agricultural implement similar to an axe, or in combat like a long-bladed knife. The blade is typically 30 to 45 centimetres (12 to 18 in) long and usually under 3 millimetres (0.12 in) thick. In the Spanish language, the word is possibly a diminutive form of the word macho, which was used to refer to sledgehammers.  This variant is the Russian Spetsnaz machete and helps with plant work speed and harvest yields.

A machete is a broad blade used either as an agricultural implement similar to an axe, or in combat like a long-bladed knife. The blade is typically 30 to 45 centimetres (12 to 18 in) long and usually under 3 millimetres (0.12 in) thick. In the Spanish language, the word is possibly a diminutive form of the word macho, which was used to refer to sledgehammers.  This variant is the Tactical OPS Steel Eagle machete and helps with plant work speed and harvest yields.

Based off the traditional maid outfit, the broad apron and attractive cuffs disguise small motors that assist in cleaning and other common household tasks. Popular with the Urbworld elite who wish to preserve traditional charm while pragmatically utilizing technology to enhance their staff.

The Makarov pistol or PM (Russian:  , Pistolet Makarova, literally Makarov's Pistol) is a Russian semi-automatic pistol. Under the project leadership of Nikolay Fyodorovich Makarov, it became the Soviet Union's standard military and police side arm in 1951.
A Rolled dish of cold cooked rice served with a garnish of raw fish, vegetables, or egg.   Food Effects: Metabolism and Manipulation.
One of the biggest varieties of pumpkin, the mammoth gold can grow to between 25 and 50 Kg of weight. Technically a giant berry, pumpkins are renowned for being trivial to both sow and harvest.

A floating, ticking time bomb that produces extremely reactive chemicals instead of chemfuel. Arguably more of a complex chemical distillery than an animal, it's a scientific miracle that it doesnt explode every time it coughs. Surprisingly effective in combat in ways the enemy would really have preferred not knowing.  A humanoid hybrid with recessive boomalope genes. Thanks to its sac filled with buoyant chemicals, this hybrid never touches the ground and simply floats from location to location. Ignores terrain penalty costs and traps, while also being able to set down explosive traps of its own.  <color=#E5E54C>Gameplay effect:</color> Humanoid hybrids will periodically engage other colonists in conversation, talking about a variety of topics. This increases the social recreation needs of those they interact with by 10% (subject to diminishing returns like all joy types). If using Ideology, humanoid hybrids are subject to precepts. Set trap ability: once every 3 days the manalope can set up an explosive IED. Hovers over terrain, ignoring terrain costs, and doesn't trigger ANY traps.

What it lacks in ferocity, it makes up for in tenacity and formidable cuteness. What person, sane or insane, could reject the diplomatic arguments presented by a waist-high teddy bear with a face just begging to be pinched. Not that you actually would, as those sharp teeth remind one that it very likely prefers to debate with its food before eating it.  A humanoid hybrid with recessive ursine genes. Absolutely terrible in combat potential despite its genetic material, but it is surprisingly adept at convincing prisoners to join the colony.  <color=#E5E54C>Gameplay effect:</color> Humanoid hybrids will periodically engage other colonists in conversation, talking about a variety of topics. This increases the social recreation needs of those they interact with by 10% (subject to diminishing returns like all joy types). If using Ideology, humanoid hybrids are subject to precepts. Menbear are adept conversationalists and will help in recruiting prisoners.

A creature originally designed for other recreational purposes before that particular laboratory of degenerates got glassed from orbit, they make for an affectionate conversation partner. You know, probably, most likely, until their particular speech pattern grinds on your nerves like a cheese grater.  A humanoid hybrid with recessive feline genes. A surprisingly large yet timid predator that can output a disturbing amount of damage. Typically fun to talk to, but 10% of the time it tries to be a little too cute.  <color=#E5E54C>Gameplay effect:</color> Like all cat hybrids, they have an improved melee dodge ability and a short nuzzle period. Humanoid hybrids will periodically engage other colonists in conversation, talking about a variety of topics. This increases the social recreation needs of those they interact with (subject to diminishing returns like all joy types). In the case of the mancat, these interactions will 90% of the time increase the targets' social joy by 15%, but the rest of the time they'll just make the target very annoyed... If using Ideology, humanoid hybrids are subject to precepts.

You know how, like, chicken tastes, like, so good? So what if, like, we made a chicken that, yknow, when you killed it you could, I dunno, stuff it right in your mouth as fried chicken? Dude, this shit is the shit, where did you get this, man? - Recording playback used in a hearing against a disgraced genetic scientist for misappropriating government funding.  A humanoid hybrid with recessive avian genes. A very valuable hybrid that convinces people that its greatest desire in life is to be eaten. When butchered, it leaves large amounts of completely healthy and nutritious meat that can be eaten as-is.  <color=#E5E54C>Gameplay effect:</color> Humanoid hybrids will periodically engage other colonists in conversation, talking about a variety of topics. This increases the social recreation needs of those they interact with by 10% (subject to diminishing returns like all joy types). If using Ideology, humanoid hybrids are subject to precepts. Doesn't lay eggs, but can be butchered for large amounts of a very nutritive meat that doesn't have poisoning chance and takes 6 days to rot.

A small citrus tree with fruit resembling miniature oranges, usually eaten plain or in fruit salads. Mandarins are smaller and oblate, rather than spherical, like the common oranges (which are a mandarin hybrid). The taste is considered less sour, as well as sweeter and stronger.

Considered a straight upgrade from their progenitor, featured several times in Cannibal Monthly. Produces appreciable amounts of wool and milk, it is a living, breathing reference to the phrase what does not kill me makes me stronger. At least, when it comes to hauling large loads, which is all some people care about.  A humanoid hybrid with recessive muffalo genes. Capable of surviving very high temperatures in opposition to the traditional use of muffalos, this hybrid performs below average for a pack animal. However, due to adaptive muscle and skeletal structure, the more it participates as part of a caravan, the heavier the load it can withstand.  <color=#E5E54C>Gameplay effect:</color> Humanoid hybrids will periodically engage other colonists in conversation, talking about a variety of topics. This increases the social recreation needs of those they interact with by 10% (subject to diminishing returns like all joy types). If using Ideology, humanoid hybrids are subject to precepts. The manffalo starts as a poor caravaning animal, but learns as time progresses. Every hour spent in a caravan will increase its cargo capacity by 1%, up to a maximum of a 100% increase from base.

The Mannlicher Ultra Light is a bolt action rifle produced by Steyr Mannlicher. The rifle has versions chambered in .222 Rem., 223 Rem., .243 Win., .308 Win. and 7mm-08 Rem. It's magazine capacity can fit up to 4 cartridges and was designed to be a lightweight option from other Mannlicher rifles.

The MannlicherSchnauer (sometimes Anglicized as "Mannlicher Schoenauer", Hellenized as / , plon/Tyfkion Mannlicher) is a type of rotary-magazine bolt-action rifle produced by Steyr Mannlicher for the Greek Army in 1903 and later was also used in small numbers by the Austro-Hungarian Army. It was the main rifle of the Hellenic Army during the first half of the 20th century. Post war use was for civilian use, such as hunting and target practice. It's magazine capacity can hold up to 5 cartridges.

They say you can learn a lot by taking something apart and putting it back together again. Not this creature, it doesnt give a damn, it just wants to take things apart because the hardest part is someone elses problem. Some people actually prefer these chitinous creatures over actual humans as theyre not going to use up good material in a botched attempt.  An insectoid hybrid with recessive humanoid genes. Easy to train, quite resilient but not a great combatant. This particular hybrid fills the niche of fulfilling deconstruction orders around the colony, freeing up otherwise valuable manpower.  <color=#E5E54C>Gameplay effect:</color> Humanoid hybrids will periodically engage other colonists in conversation, talking about a variety of topics. This increases the social recreation needs of those they interact with by 10% (subject to diminishing returns like all joy types). If using Ideology, humanoid hybrids are subject to precepts. All insectoid hybrids have good armor and no toxic sensitivity, but they are always sterile and can't reproduce, even if a fertility booster is used to create them. Menscarab will take building deconstruction orders around the colony.

A bloody weird little thing that hates the cold with a passion, and will take any opportunity to clear away snow from its home. Given that they are active at nighttime, they make a great conversational companion for those otherwise asocial Night Owls you keep gathering.  A humanoid hybrid with recessive rodent genes. Quite quick for their size and unusually a nocturnal animal, they make for a fast, social and quick-breeding hybrid. Will shovel snow if there are Clear Snow zones set up.  <color=#E5E54C>Gameplay effect:</color> Humanoid hybrids will periodically engage other colonists in conversation, talking about a variety of topics. This increases the social recreation needs of those they interact with by 10% (subject to diminishing returns like all joy types). If using Ideology, humanoid hybrids are subject to precepts. The mansquirrel is a nocturnal animal that sleeps during the day. Will obey orders to clear snow around the colony.

Possibly either the ancestor to the warg or an attempt at creating a successor, the team in charge of making this particular hybrid clearly had read one to many mythological novels. Arguably theres no transformation at the full moon, so you just get the permanent single form, but theres no pleasing some people.  A humanoid hybrid with recessive canine genes. A fast and dangerous hunter with almost misplaced self-confidence. Also very intelligent and possessing faint regenerative capabilities. Extremely hardy but also extremely restrictive in their diet.  <color=#E5E54C>Gameplay effect:</color> Humanoid hybrids will periodically engage other colonists in conversation, talking about a variety of topics. This increases the social recreation needs of those they interact with by 10% (subject to diminishing returns like all joy types). If using Ideology, humanoid hybrids are subject to precepts.
A thick emulsion of egg, oil, and other herbs. Mayonnaise, while terrible for you, adds a pleasing tang and is very calorically dense.
The MD97 is a selective-fire or semi-automatic assault rifle that has been produced by IMBEL in Brazil since 1997. It is based upon the IMBEL MD2, which is itself based upon the FN FAL.
This is a tall tray rack; haulers carry meals and treats here for storage.

A tall metal frame with several hooks hanging from chains.  A simple crank allows hoisting several hanging things into the air.  A way to store the dead bodies of fellow animals you have killed, before cutting them up and consuming their flesh.  You monster.  Note that you can only fit so many giant corpses into one space, even if you stack them.  The frame will only hold so much weight.
A simple baked pie with a filling of meat.   Food Effects: BloodPumping.
A mechanoid cheese created by pressing mechanoid milk. This isn't edible, but if consumed it will act as an incredibly powerful drug, similar to Luciferium, but without addictiveness.

This cybernetic beast has been mutated far beyond its original form. Heavily armoured to withstand heavy fire, and armed with a terrifying plasma cannon.  <color=#E5E54C>Gameplay effect:</color>Mechanoid hybrids are always created with a controller booster, making the mechabear an effective weapons platform, akin to a rocket turret. Mechanoid hybrids need very little food or rest, don't have psychic or toxic sensitivity, and have devastating ranged attacks. They have however high wildness, making them harder to keep tamed, and they will need a mechahybrid antenna to be built somewhere on the planet, or their IFF sensors will malfunction in 5 days. One antenna is needed for each five mech hybrids under the colony's control.

The tail of this robotic creature has been crafted from an amalgamation of scyther blade structures and mechanite self-replicators. This allows the mechacat to use its tail as a throwable weapon, and quickly regenerate it to use it again.   <color=#E5E54C>Gameplay effect:</color>Mechanoid hybrids are always created with a controller booster, making the mechacat capable of attacking with slashing attacks from a range. Mechanoid hybrids need very little food or rest, don't have psychic or toxic sensitivity, and have devastating ranged attacks. They have however high wildness, making them harder to keep tamed, and they will need a mechahybrid antenna to be built somewhere on the planet, or their IFF sensors will malfunction in 5 days. One antenna is needed for each five mech hybrids under the colony's control.

This cybernetic organism is adept at reconnaissance and infiltration, due to its small size and speed. It is armed with a small sniper flechette gun.   <color=#E5E54C>Gameplay effect:</color> Mechanoid hybrids are always created with a controller booster, making the mecha-chicken an effective weapons platform with very long range sniper attacks. Mechanoid hybrids need very little food or rest, don't have psychic or toxic sensitivity, and have devastating ranged attacks. They have however high wildness, making them harder to keep tamed, and they will need a mechahybrid antenna to be built somewhere on the planet, or their IFF sensors will malfunction in 5 days. One antenna is needed for each five mech hybrids under the colony's control.

A drug for preventing mechanites before they take hold. Blocks fibrous and sensory mechanites. Must be taken every 5 days to remain effective.  This drug only prevents new infections. It does not cure existing infections - even those that are not yet discovered.

More machine than horse, the mecha-horse has an agile frame covered by ablative panels. Though well-liked by riders for its speed and agility, it has a significant design flaw: it heats up considerably during extended travels, needing to periodically vent excess heated air generated on their internal machinery.  <color=#E5E54C>Gameplay effect:</color>Mechanoid hybrids are always created with a controller booster, making the mecha-horse capable of using its "vent heated exhaust" ability to scorch enemies on the surrounding tiles. Mechanoid hybrids need very little food or rest, don't have psychic or toxic sensitivity, and have devastating ranged attacks. They have however high wildness, making them harder to keep tamed, and they will need a mechahybrid antenna to be built somewhere on the planet, or their IFF sensors will malfunction in 5 days. One antenna is needed for each five mech hybrids under the colony's control.

This cybernetic boomalope has been outfitted with four mechanized chemfuel reservoirs. The creature can use these reservoirs to produce a jet of burning fuel similar to a flamethrower, not incredibly harmful, but perfect for starting huge fires.  <color=#E5E54C>Gameplay effect:</color> Mechanoid hybrids are always created with a controller booster, making the mechalope an effective weapons platform, akin to a flamethrower. Mechanoid hybrids need very little food or rest, don't have psychic or toxic sensitivity, and have devastating ranged attacks. They have however high wildness, making them harder to keep tamed, and they will need a mechahybrid antenna to be built somewhere on the planet, or their IFF sensors will malfunction in 5 days. One antenna is needed for each five mech hybrids under the colony's control.

The ultimate violation of all ethical concerns in genetic engineering: a humanlike mechanoid creature with obvious malevolence. Created by warping humanoid genes into a dangerous Mime, and then further modifying it with self-replicating mechanites by using forgotten technology, the mecha-mime will need to be kept in a short leash, lest its IFF system goes haywire and decides to enact its very own judgement day.  <color=#E5E54C>Gameplay effect:</color>Mechanoid hybrids are always created with a controller booster. The mecha-mime has lost the infiltration abilities of a regular mime, but in exchange it possesses a powerful spatial warping cannon that ignores enemy's armor. Mechanoid hybrids need very little food or rest, don't have psychic or toxic sensitivity, and have devastating ranged attacks. They have however high wildness, making them harder to keep tamed, and they will need a mechahybrid antenna to be built somewhere on the planet, or their IFF sensors will malfunction in 5 days. One antenna is needed for each five mech hybrids under the colony's control.  <color=#E5E54C>Warning:</color> A mecha-mime's IFF sensors will fail in only 2 days, instead of 5.

This hulking cybernetic organism has been reinforced with an adaptive plasteel mesh, enabling it to carry an incredible amount of stuff. The mecha-muffalo is the perfect pack animal, but it is quite useless in an offensive role. Defensively, however, it is armed with a smoke cannon that it can use to cover the battlefield in a dense cloud of dust.  <color=#E5E54C>Gameplay effect:</color> Mechanoid hybrids are always created with a controller booster, making the mecha-muffalo capable of laying a screen of smoke for defensive purposes. Mechanoid hybrids need very little food or rest, don't have psychic or toxic sensitivity, and have devastating ranged attacks. They have however high wildness, making them harder to keep tamed, and they will need a mechahybrid antenna to be built somewhere on the planet, or their IFF sensors will malfunction in 5 days. One antenna is needed for each five mech hybrids under the colony's control.
This highly sought-after booster will result in an almost perfect hybrid: fertile, draftable and genetically stable.  This booster can't be crafted, only scavenged.
A self-contained mechanite factory designed to produce disassembler mechanites.

This strange stellated octahedron seems to house an assembly of complex computer chips. It appears to be self-powered, and a faint beeping noise emanates from its core. It is constantly emitting encoded radio waves, and perhaps these could be suitably amplified if the technology behind it could be properly reverse engineered.  <color=#E5E54C>Gameplay effect:</color> Mechanoid chips can only be found in abandoned labs, and can be used to build biomechanical lab beacons, that will allow you to find a biomechanical lab complex, as well as mechahybrid antennas.

This diminutive egg seems to be metallic in nature at first, yet it is soft enough to crush it between two fingers. Once thus crushed it can be swallowed normally, and the active mechanites inside have a reinvigorating effect on the consumer. This effect can be slightly addictive, though.
This metallic, quicksilver-like substance is not edible. It can be processed in a refinery to obtain neutroamine, chemfuel and a bit of silver.
This wool seems to be strengthened by plasteel micro-fibers, and covered with advanced circuitry.

This tiny cybernetic organism can be mass-produced as a kind of "suicide weapon". It is very fast, and armed with a short ranged stun gun, so hordes of mecha-rats can be sent to the front lines to keep enemies stunned and in check.   <color=#E5E54C>Gameplay effect:</color>Mechanoid hybrids are always created with a controller booster, allowing the colonists to send the mecha-rat to the front lines to quickly stun enemies. Mechanoid hybrids need very little food or rest, don't have psychic or toxic sensitivity, and have devastating ranged attacks. They have however high wildness, making them harder to keep tamed, and they will need a mechahybrid antenna to be built somewhere on the planet, or their IFF sensors will malfunction in 5 days. One antenna is needed for each five mech hybrids under the colony's control.

This cybernetic organism has traits from both its insectoid and mechanoid origins. The mechaspider is armed with a powerful twin-coiled laser machine gun, perfect to obliterate enemies in a rain of laser fire.  <color=#E5E54C>Gameplay effect:</color> Mechanoid hybrids are always created with a controller booster, making the mechaspider an effective weapons platform with a very high fire rate. Mechanoid hybrids need very little food or rest, don't have psychic or toxic sensitivity, and have devastating ranged attacks. They have however high wildness, making them harder to keep tamed, and they will need a mechahybrid antenna to be built somewhere on the planet, or their IFF sensors will malfunction in 5 days. One antenna is needed for each five mech hybrids under the colony's control.

This hulking cybernetic behemoth is why you don't need tanks in the Rim. Its huge plasteel carapace hides a miniaturized synchrotron that constantly generates small amounts of antimatter, which is instantly used to fill a miniature antigrain warhead. Slow, but quite effective.  <color=#E5E54C>Gameplay effect:</color>Mechanoid hybrids are always created with a controller booster, making the mechathrumbo effective mobile artillery. Mechanoid hybrids need very little food or rest, don't have psychic or toxic sensitivity, and have devastating ranged attacks. They have however high wildness, making them harder to keep tamed, and they will need a mechahybrid antenna to be built somewhere on the planet, or their IFF sensors will malfunction in 5 days. One antenna is needed for each five mech hybrids under the colony's control.

This slow, cybernetic beast is heavily armoured with a plasteel-encased biomechanical shell. It is armed with a poison spitting cannon.  <color=#E5E54C>Gameplay effect:</color>Mechanoid hybrids are always created with a controller booster, making the mechaturtle an effective weapons platform that fires venomous projectiles. Mechanoid hybrids need very little food or rest, don't have psychic or toxic sensitivity, and have devastating ranged attacks. They have however high wildness, making them harder to keep tamed, and they will need a mechahybrid antenna to be built somewhere on the planet, or their IFF sensors will malfunction in 5 days. One antenna is needed for each five mech hybrids under the colony's control.

This cybernetic beast has been augmented with a powerful synthetic structure capable of generating waves of cryogenic liquid.   <color=#E5E54C>Gameplay effect:</color>Mechanoid hybrids are always created with a controller booster, making the mechawolf an effective weapons platform that fires frost projectiles. Mechanoid hybrids need very little food or rest, don't have psychic or toxic sensitivity, and have devastating ranged attacks. They have however high wildness, making them harder to keep tamed, and they will need a mechahybrid antenna to be built somewhere on the planet, or their IFF sensors will malfunction in 5 days. One antenna is needed for each five mech hybrids under the colony's control.
A set of cabinets and shelves for stocking medicines and drugs.  Recommended: keep an eye on children.

The MG 42 (shortened from German: Maschinengewehr 42, or "machine gun 42") is a 7.9257mm Mauser general-purpose machine gun designed in Nazi Germany and used extensively by the Wehrmacht and the Waffen-SS during the second half of World War II. Entering production in 1942, it was intended to supplement and replace the earlier MG 34, which was more expensive and took much longer to produce, but both weapons were produced until the end of World War II.
A small muscle-powered grinding stone for grinding raw plants.

The Mk 14 Enhanced Battle Rifle (EBR) is an American selective fire military designated marksman rifle chambered for the 7.6251mm NATO cartridge.    It is a variant of the M14 battle rifle and was originally built for use with units of United States Special Operations Command, such as the United States Navy SEALs, Delta Force, and task specific ODA teams/units.

The Mk 14 Enhanced Battle Rifle (EBR) is an American selective fire military designated marksman rifle chambered for the 7.6251mm NATO cartridge.    It is a variant of the M14 battle rifle and was originally built for use with units of United States Special Operations Command, such as the United States Navy SEALs, Delta Force, and task specific ODA teams/units.

The Winchester Model 1897, also known as the Model 97, M97, or Trench Gun, was a pump-action shotgun with an external hammer and tube magazine manufactured by the Winchester Repeating Arms Company. The Model 1897 was an evolution of the Winchester Model 1893 designed by John Browning. From 1897 until 1957, over one million of these shotguns were produced. The Model 1897 was offered in numerous barrel lengths and grades, chambered in 12 and 16 gauge, and as a solid frame or takedown.

The Remington Model 870 is a pump-action shotgun manufactured by Remington Arms Company, LLC. It is widely used by the public for sport shooting, hunting, and self-defense and used by law enforcement and military organizations worldwide.

Far too independent to be a combat animal but certainly can both dish out and take pain. Works best in the background, minding its own business and digging up metals it finds. No one is really sure why but it probably has to do with those massive whiskers.  A rodent hybrid with recessive ursine genes. An independent predator with a very low metabolism and high toughness. Has an unusual behaviour where itll periodically dig for treasures, typically raw metals.  <color=#E5E54C>Gameplay effect:</color> All rodent hybrids have fast gestation, as long as a fertility unblocker was used when creating them in the genomorpher.

An oversized naked mole-rat with frighteningly large chompers, however theyre not as dangerous as they look as they are quite timid and use said teeth for chewing up tough vegetables. Objectively cute when you give them a good brushing, but have a nasty habit of overshooting hand-fed snacks and biting on hands due to poor eyesight. A saddle is recommended for riding, as there is little fat and no fur to cushion their boney structure and loose skin.  An equine hybrid with recessive rodent genes. Quite small and lacking in durability, but surprisingly capable as a mount. Exceedingly filthy for an animal that eats so little, however this is tied to its rapid gestation and faint regenerative capabilities.  <color=#E5E54C>Gameplay effect:</color> All equine hybrids are good for caravaning. A caravan with one of them needs a shorter resting period, only stopping to rest between 23:30 PM and 4 AM.

A hulking monstrosity that is genuinely caring for those around them, taking great joy and actual personal pleasure through working diligently and caring for those it considers friends and family. Evidently, it was bred specifically by megacorporations to work in dangerous mines, because human greed never changes.  A rodent hybrid with recessive humanoid genes. Very low hunger rate and very intelligent, these gentle giants enjoy digging with their hands. They will sometimes work mining orders given the chance but theyre very slow due to their bulk.  <color=#E5E54C>Gameplay effect:</color> Humanoid hybrids will periodically engage other colonists in conversation, talking about a variety of topics. This increases the social recreation needs of those they interact with by 10% (subject to diminishing returns like all joy types). If using Ideology, humanoid hybrids are subject to precepts. Molemen will periodically obey commands to mine. This will also work with the Quarry mod.

The 3-line rifle M1891, colloquially known as MosinNagant is a five-shot, bolt-action, internal magazinefed, military rifle developed from 1882 to 1891, and used by the armed forces of the Russian Empire, the Soviet Union and various other nations.   It is one of the most mass-produced military bolt-action rifles in history with over 37 million units having been made since its inception in 1891, and, in spite of its age, it has been used in various conflicts around the world up to the modern day.

Mossberg 500 is a series of pump action shotguns manufactured by O.F. Mossberg and Sons. The 500 series comprises widely varying models of hammerless repeaters, all of which share the same basic receiver and action, but differ in bore size, barrel length, choke options, magazine capacity, stock and forearm materials.

The MP-412 REX (Revolver for Export; Russian: MP-412 ) is a Russian double-action/single-action revolver designed by the state-owned Izhevsk Mechanical Plant (IZHMEKH), with a break-action chamber and an automatic ejector, chambered for the .357 Magnum round.

The MP5 (German: Maschinenpistole 5) is a 9mm submachine gun, developed in the 1960s by a team of engineers from the German small arms manufacturer Heckler and Koch GmbH (HK) of Oberndorf am Neckar. There are over 100 variants of the MP5, including some semi-automatic versions.  The MP5 is one of the most widely used submachine guns in the world, having been adopted by 40 nations and numerous military, law enforcement, intelligence, and security organizations. It is widely used by SWAT teams in North America.  In 1999, Heckler and Koch developed the Heckler and Koch UMP, the MP5's successor

The MP5 (German: Maschinenpistole 5) is a 9mm submachine gun, developed in the 1960s by a team of engineers from the German small arms manufacturer Heckler and Koch GmbH (HK) of Oberndorf am Neckar. There are over 100 variants of the MP5, including some semi-automatic versions.  The MP5 is one of the most widely used submachine guns in the world, having been adopted by 40 nations and numerous military, law enforcement, intelligence, and security organizations. It is widely used by SWAT teams in North America.  In 1999, Heckler and Koch developed the Heckler and Koch UMP, the MP5's successor

The Heckler and Koch MP7 (Maschinenpistole 7) is a German personal defence weapon (PDW) designed and manufactured by Heckler and Koch (HK) and chambered for the HK 4.630mm cartridge. It was designed with the new cartridge to meet NATO requirements published in 1989, as these requirements call for a personal defense weapon (PDW) class firearm, with a greater ability to penetrate body armor than current weapons limited to conventional pistol cartridges. The MP7 went into production in 2001. It is a direct rival to the FN P90, also developed in response to NATO's requirement. The weapon has been revised since its introduction and the latest production variants are the MP7A1 and MP7A2.

A payload of muffalo genetic material. Can be used at the genomorpher to create a growth cell of a hybrid animal. This tier 1 genome can be used as either a primary or secondary genome.  <color=#E5E54C>Gameplay effect:</color> All muffalo hybrid animals are pack animals, with primary muffalo hybrids getting 50% increased capacity caravaning. All muffalo hybrids have an increase to minimum comfortable temperature.  <color=#E5E54C>Extraction:</color> Can be extracted via the genome extractor table or any genome excavator from:

Directly injects muffalo genes in an humanoid. This genetrainer gives the wild attunement health state, increasing plant work speed, carrying capacity, foraging and... leather amount.  Genetrainers are implants that do not take the place of any given organ. Only one can be "installed" at a time. Using a second genetrainer will have no effect. Bear in mind that a genetrainer modifies the genes of the human subject, and only death will get rid of its effects.

A return to simpler times, when everyone could have sworn blind that muffalos used to be able to produce milk but were instead fooled by hornless paragons.  A perfect muffalo animal, paragon of all similar animals with no needless junk genetic data. Besides the various improvements to the baseline animals abilities, this paragon also produces milk and can be slaughtered for a valuable pelt, which can either be used for decoration or sold.
Cool! You can now make your own Game of Thrones / Rimworld cosplay! Or it can also be repurposed as a comfy rug.
A muffalo pelt rug. Taxidermy seems to be in vogue on the Rim!

An absolute unit of a muffalo hybrid with muscles bursting underneath the layers of fur and fat. An excellent caravan companion for those wanting to transport lots of goods and hot muffalobear milk makes living in eternal winter seem almost worth it.  A muffalo hybrid with recessive ursine genes. While they are slower and eat more compared to a regular muffalo, they are better at self defence and offer the highest carry capacity of all primary muffalo hybrids. They also produce good thick wool and delicious yet simple milk.  <color=#E5E54C>Gameplay effect:</color> All primary muffalo hybrids have 150% carrying capacity on caravans.
A delicious milk with roasted overtones. Very pleasurable to eat, but not very nutritious.

Combining fierce independence with an animal suited for travelling long distances might not have been the best idea. But critics have clearly never been nuzzled by a giant cat only to be buried alive in a pile of insulating hair in the winter, so what do they know.  A muffalo hybrid with recessive feline genes. Not the best for caravan duty but their regular grooming produces bundles of thick wool and can be milked for a rather disgusting milk filled with hair. A low maintenance way of getting more hair than you bargained for.  <color=#E5E54C>Gameplay effect:</color> Produces wool without needing to be sheared. All primary muffalo hybrids have 150% carrying capacity on caravans. Like all cat hybrids, they have an improved melee dodge ability and a short nuzzle period.

Dont let its adorable appearance fool you, this beastie is ready to fly off its handle at a moment's notice. The more its hurt, the more pissed off it gets and the faster itll try to rip its enemies to shreds.  A muffalo hybrid with recessive avian genes. A bit too slow and weak for a caravan companion but it makes  for a vicious and suicidal protective companion. Produces a thick, chunky milk that tastes like a protein shake.  <color=#E5E54C>Gameplay effect:</color> The melee cooldown of its attacks scales with the percentage of lost health, up to 6 times faster. All primary muffalo hybrids have 150% carrying capacity on caravans.
This lumpy milk seems to have concentrated protein chunks, tasting like chicken nuggets. Disgusting, but colonists seem to like it.

Belligerent bulls with a penchant for the tastes of the wild wastes. A herd of these creatures can be occasionally seen trawling through regions, consuming practically all edible vegetation and leaving fertile waste in their path. Some argue that this is the ideal form of muffalo for nomad tribes, as they produce everything they need to survive winters and are large enough to feed said tribe through the harshest of seasons.  An equine hybrid with recessive muffalo genes. Very unusual in that it doesnt help a caravan speed along, largely due to it excessively foraging and eating various vegetation from new locations, as well as roughage to help with digestion. The benefit from this behaviour is that this stimulation is the only way itll produce milk and wool, so herds of these hybrids can be taken on a long journey to provide produce vital to small and starting colonies.  <color=#E5E54C>Gameplay effect:</color> All equine hybrids are good for caravaning. A caravan with one of them needs a shorter resting period, only stopping to rest between 23:30 PM and 4 AM.

Milking snakes for venom in order to create medicine is an extremely dangerous career. While this particular beast of burden proved to be capable in other areas, it was mainly synthesised in order to provide a safer way of sourcing an anaesthetic coagulant to be used in emergencies. Or someone was trying to get high by milking a reptilian space cow, who really knows.  A reptile hybrid with recessive muffalo genes. A strong pack animal with a massive appetite and a proportionate filth rate. Quite durable and will prove a fatal mistake for any animal that attempts to hunt them, as their fangs, horns and claws are all venomous. Can be milked every ten days for a vial of paralysing coagulant, best used for large animals that are suffering from multiple lacerations.  <color=#E5E54C>Gameplay effect:</color> All reptile hybrids have good temperature tolerance ranges and venomous attacks.

The animal weve all been waiting for, namely one that not only cleans up after itself but for others as well. Their fur is surprisingly soft and has antibacterial properties, which it uses along with its fingered paws to clean surfaces. Once the fur starts to become matted is when it needs to be trimmed.  A muffalo hybrid with recessive humanoid genes. Quite intelligent but they lose out on a lot of their progenitors hardiness against the cold. They are also very clean animals and will clean areas around the colony, and can be sheared regularly for a decent amount of wool.  <color=#E5E54C>Gameplay effect:</color> Humanoid hybrids will periodically engage other colonists in conversation, talking about a variety of topics. This increases the social recreation needs of those they interact with by 10% (subject to diminishing returns like all joy types). If using Ideology, humanoid hybrids are subject to precepts. All primary muffalo hybrids have 150% carrying capacity on caravans. Muffalomen are clean muffalo hybrids that will periodically clean around the colony.

A very naughty hybrid that can be told to relieve itself on command, creating puddles of chemfuel-infused urine around it. For those who just want to watch the world burn in the most vulgar way.  A muffalo hybrid with recessive boomalope genes. A bit too slow for a caravan companion but make up for it with intelligence and an unusual chemfuel ability that lends itself for defence.  <color=#E5E54C>Gameplay effect:</color> All primary muffalo hybrids have 150% carrying capacity on caravans.

An oversized grub with udders that extrude jelly instead of milk, its hard-headedness serves it well in both getting what it wants and nutting anyone foolish enough to think theyre better than them. Allegedly there was a case where the owner was prevented from shearing the creature for so long that the overlapping plates completely prevented it from moving, who was afterwards thanked with a kick in the nether region.  An insectoid hybrid with recessive muffalo genes. Higher metabolism compared to other insectoid hybrids as well as stubborn, any predator foolish enough to think of them as an easy meal will be responded with a headbutt like a sledgehammer. Can work as a pack animal but refuses to haul comparatively heavy loads. Regularly produces precious jelly and can be sheared for chitin, which overlaps and protects the animal well from blunt attacks.  <color=#E5E54C>Gameplay effect:</color> All insectoid hybrids have good armor and no toxic sensitivity, but they are always sterile and can't reproduce, even if a fertility booster is used to create them.

Breeding a muffalo hybrid into such a small package means they have very little capacity for either wool or milk. Theyre very quick though, and your handlers better be quicker on their daily milking and shearing.  A muffalo hybrid with recessive rodent genes. Very weak as a pack animal but they breed quickly and can be milked and sheared daily. The amount of product is small, but its thick wool and nutritious milk.  <color=#E5E54C>Gameplay effect:</color> All primary muffalo hybrids have 150% carrying capacity on caravans.

Someone clearly wanted multiple muffalos that would be capable of tearing foolish attackers to shreds. They eat a ton but those massive teeth of theirs arent just good at chewing up vegetation. Plus theyre incredibly cute when they wag their massive tails.  A muffalo hybrid with recessive canine genes. The combination of lethality, speed and high intelligence makes this hybrid a fierce pack animal, both figuratively and literally. Capable of pack tactics with other muffalowolves that further increase their melee dodge, hit chance and dps.  <color=#E5E54C>Gameplay effect:</color> The pack tactics ability will give any muffalowolves around bonuses to melee dps, melee dodge and melee hit chance. All primary muffalo hybrids have 150% carrying capacity on caravans.
A sweet baked muffin made with fruit.   Food Effects: Well Fed: Baked Good.    Increased Consciousness and Metabolism
Raw protein-rich mushrooms. Nice to eat, even when raw.
Beautiful Yellow-Orange Petals from the Neutro Flower. Used to make Neutroamine, a medicine base.
A small ball of rice topped with raw fish or other seafood.   Food Effects: BloodPumping.

The Next generation Light Anti-tank Weapon (NLAW) or the Next Generation Light Anti-Armour Weapon, also known as the MBT LAW or the RB 57, is a fire-and-forget, lightweight shoulder-fired, and disposable (single-use) line of sight (LOS) missile system, designed for infantry use.     The missile is using a soft-launch system and is guided by predicted line of sight (PLOS). It can carry out an overfly top attack (OTA) on an armoured vehicle, or a direct attack (DA) on structures and non-armoured vehicles.

A slurry of liquefied organic pulp fills this reinforced glass vat. This solution is used by genetic experiments, and increases work speed when placed near a Vanilla Genetics Expanded workbench. One workbench can use to up to two nutrient vats.
A small berry fruit that grows on trees.
An edible bulb of pungent, savory taste and smell with almost as many varieties as cooking applications.
A sweet fruit that grows on trees.

The OTs-03 SVU (Russian:   , Snayperskaya Vintovka Ukorochennaya, Sniper Rifle Shortened) is a bullpup configuration of the SVD sniper rifle.    The SVU was developed to meet the needs of the security forces of the Russian Ministry of Internal Affairs, such as OMON. The SVU was first seen in use in the First Chechen War. Originally, the plan was to just slightly modernize the aging SVD, but the designers eventually realised that the configuration of the weapon would have to be completely altered, leading to the creation of the SVU.
A stone oven used for baking.

The SIG Sauer P226 is a full-sized, service-type pistol made by SIG Sauer. It is chambered for the 919mm Parabellum, .40 S&W, .357 SIG, and .22 Long Rifle. It is essentially the same basic design of the SIG Sauer P220, but developed to use higher capacity, double stack magazines in place of the single stack magazines of the P220.

The SIG Sauer P226 is a full-sized, service-type pistol made by SIG Sauer. It is chambered for the 919mm Parabellum, .40 S&W, .357 SIG, and .22 Long Rifle. It is essentially the same basic design of the SIG Sauer P220, but developed to use higher capacity, double stack magazines in place of the single stack magazines of the P220.

The SIG Sauer P320 is a modular design of semi-automatic pistol made by Sig Sauer, Inc. of Exeter, New Hampshire and SIG Sauer GmbH of Eckernfrde, Germany.   On 19 January 2017, it was announced that a customized version of the SIG Sauer P320 had won the United States Army's XM17 Modular Handgun System competition.
A flat pallet for packing things.  Does not protect against the weather.  Sometimes difficult to manage, but useful nonetheless.

A flat pallet for packing things.  Wrapping things up in thick oilcloth keeps items secure and organized.  You can pack more types of things on this pallet because you can wrap items together, altho this slows you down a little.

The Pancor Corporation Jackhammer is a 12-gauge, blow-forward gas-operated bullpup automatic shotgun designed in 1984 and patented in 1987. Only three working prototypes of the Jackhammer were built. Nonetheless, its distinctive aesthetics and futuristic design have made it a prop in action films, television programs, and video games.
A sweet fruit that grows on trees.
Crispy green pears. While at first similar to apples, pears are slightly more fibrous and less sweet.
Spherical green seeds tucked safely away in a fleshy pod. Peas are notable for having potentially long shelf-lives when dried properly.

Tiny, spicy, crimson pods often used in sauces, relishes, or powders. While the flavor itself is mild the capsaicin contained inside means humans find them oddly addicting, if painful when consumed in mass. Animals are known to avoid eating the plant entirely.
Vegetables that have been preserved in a salty brine.
A tropical fruit having large swordlike leaves and a large, fleshy, edible, multiple fruit with a terminal tuft of leaves.
Glass bottles filled with a strange pink substance. The spore suggested that you throw these at your enemies.
Pizza in 30 minutes or less!   Food Effects: Well Fed: Baked Good.    Increased Consciousness and Metabolism

The PK (Russian:  , or "Kalashnikov's Machinegun"), is a 7.62x54mmR general-purpose machine gun designed in the Soviet Union and currently in production in Russia.  The original PK was a development of Kalashnikov's AKM assault rifle and the accompanying RPK light machine gun design that featured stamped receivers. The PK uses the 7.62x54mmR Eastern Bloc standard cartridge.

A smooth-skinned purple fruit. Many cultures dry-age plums into prunes for long-term preservation. Instead of rotting, once the 15 days have passed the plums will dry into prunes, which are considered preserved food.

This tiny vial is filled with a concentrated solution of Muffalokomodo saliva, which acts as a powerful neuromuscular-blocking drug. This effectively paralyses anyone that drinks it, though it is not lethal. It will also stop bleeding rate while active, perhaps allowing a person to avoid bleeding to death if the poison is administered quick enough. Effects wear off after 6 hours.
A simple porridge cooked from grains.   Food Effects: BloodPumping.

A highly advanced artificial brain made using cutting edge ultratech techniques.  This sophisticated computation device is designed to house a human or artificial intelligence.  Its design elevates a persons consciousness to an entirely new level greatly increasing their cognitive abilities.  Its primarily used to transfer a persons consciousness to fight against the slow endless march of time and its effects on organic body parts.  Its as hard as plasteel and through the use of a lattice-dust healing system its capable of repairing itself over time.  Warning: Due to the nature of its design it is incompatible with brain implants.

The Bizon ("Bison") is a 9mm submachine gun developed in 1993 at Izhmash by a team of engineers headed by Victor Kalashnikov (son of engineer Mikhail Kalashnikov, creator of the AK-47 and AK-74). Alexei Dragunov, youngest son of Evgeny Dragunov (the creator of the SVD sniper rifle), was also a member of the design team.

The PPSh-41 (pistolet-pulemyot Shpagina; Russian: - ; "Shpagin machine pistol"); is a Soviet submachine gun designed by Georgy Shpagin as a cheap, reliable, and simplified alternative to the PPD-40.     Common nicknames are "pe-pe-sha" (Russian: ) from its three-letter acronym and "papasha" (Russian: ), meaning "daddy".
Pink, melon-like edible fruits, used historically for both snacking as well as medicine by desert natives.
A eye prosthesis. It's not as efficient as the real thing but it's better than the nothing.
A foot prosthesis. While it lacks a neural interface, its complex arrangement of internal joints allows it to mimic natural movement quite convincingly. Still, it is inferior to a real foot.
A hand prosthesis. While it lacks a neural interface, its complex arrangement of internal joints allows it to mimic natural movement quite convincingly. Still, it is inferior to a real hand.
A kidney prosthesis. It's not as efficient as the real thing but it's better than the nothing.
A liver prosthesis. It's not as efficient as the real thing but it's better than the nothing.
A lung prosthesis. It's not as efficient as the real thing but it's better than the nothing.
A spine prosthesis. It's not as efficient as the real thing but it's better than the nothing.
A stomach prosthesis. It's not as efficient as the real thing but it's better than the nothing.
Dried plums. Prunes take a very long time to deteriorate.

The PSG1 (Przisionsschtzengewehr, German for "precision shooter rifle") is a semi-automatic sniper rifle designed and produced by the German company Heckler and Koch of Oberndorf am Neckar.   This rifle is said to have been developed in response to the Munich massacre at the 1972 Summer Olympics. The West German police units could not engage the terrorists quickly enough to prevent them from killing their hostages. HK was then commissioned to create a high accuracy, large magazine capacity, semi-automatic rifle for police and military use.

The PSL (Romanian: Puc Semiautomat 7,62 mm cu Lunet, model 1974, "scoped semi-automatic rifle") is a Romanian military designated marksman rifle. It is also called PSL-54C, Romak III, FPK and SSG-97 (Scharfschtzengewehr 1997). Though similar in appearance, mission and specifications to the SVD Dragunov, the PSL rifle is mechanically completely different and based on the RPK light machine gun.
A large psychic effector capable of disrupting the minds of distant foes. Can be used to construct a spinal weapon.
Gives limited telekinetic ability, allowing the user to lift or move small objects. This improves manipulation, with an effect proportional to psychic sensitivity.

Gives limited mind-reading ability, allowing the user to track enemies' movements before they make them. This improves melee dodge chance and shooting accuracy, with an effect proportional to psychic sensitivity.

A dose of semi-coherent mechanites which work as a conduit across the body to enhance the hosts psychic abilities.  Due to how mechanites work only one strain can exist harmoniously inside the hosts body.  However, it is possible to remove a mechanite strain with an expensive and difficult surgery.

The Taurus PT92 is a double action/single action, 9mm, double-stack magazine-fed, short recoil-operated, semi-automatic pistol manufactured by Taurus in the former Beretta factory in So Paulo, Brazil.  This version comes in a Special Forces (SF) configuration.

The FAL (French: Fusil Automatique Lger, English: Light Automatic Rifle) is a battle rifle designed by Belgian small arms designers Dieudonn Saive and Ernest Vervier and manufactured by FN Herstal.  During the Cold War the FAL was adopted by many countries of the North Atlantic Treaty Organization (NATO), with the notable exception of the United States. It is one of the most widely used rifles in history, having been used by more than 90 countries. Because of its prevalence and widespread usage among the militaries of many NATO and first world countries during the Cold War it was given the title "The right arm of the Free World".  The FAL was produced under licence in South Africa by Lyttleton Engineering Works, where it is known as the R1. After a competition between the German G3 rifle, the Armalite AR-10, and the FN FAL, the South African Defence Force adopted three main variants of the FAL: a rifle with the designation R1, a "lightweight" variant of the FN FAL 50.64 with folding butt, fabricated locally under the designation R2, and a model designed for police use not capable of automatic fire under the designation R3.

For a combination of two relatively small animals, the rabbitcat is fucking massive and has a robust physique. It knows no fear and will tackle anything it wants to eat. Some say this was the other attempt to create the Rabbit of Caerbannog, because who says geneticists dont have a sick sense of humour.  A rodent hybrid with recessive feline genes. Very intelligent considering the source material, these hybrids are fast, lethal and possess a robust physique with rapid natural regenerative capabilities. Quite stubborn so they require frequent, competent training but they arent afraid to show their appreciation.  <color=#E5E54C>Gameplay effect:</color> Like all cat hybrids, they have an improved melee dodge ability and a short nuzzle period. All rodent hybrids have fast gestation, as long as a fertility unblocker was used when creating them in the genomorpher.

Legends say of an ancient and vicious monster, a creature so foul, so cruel that no man yet has fought with it and lived. This was a somewhat successful attempt, as its weakness lulls the enemy into a false sense of security so that it can rip their throat out. So do you feel lucky, punk?  A rodent hybrid with recessive avian genes. A tiny, weak, fast-moving pest with an insane appetite for its size. Incredibly fast gestation period and a 1% chance to instantly kill when attacking.  <color=#E5E54C>Gameplay effect:</color> All rodent hybrids have fast gestation, as long as a fertility unblocker was used when creating them in the genomorpher.
Heats rooms using hot water from boilers. Requires 100 heating units.
Once you get over the thought that this cheese was created from giant rat milk, it isn't so bad at all!

An interesting pack animal that packs an incredible punch that also pisses and shits everywhere. That aint even the worst part, because these rodents of unusual size are also plague carriers with complete immunity to toxicity. Sometimes scientists just cant leave well enough alone.  A rodent hybrid with recessive muffalo genes. Quite clever, almost absurdly lethal and quick on its feet. While they are herbivores, they will still happily munch on corpses thanks to their large appetite. Not as short a gestation period compared to other primary rodent hybrids, but every bite transmits the plague.  <color=#E5E54C>Gameplay effect:</color> All rodent hybrids have fast gestation, as long as a fertility unblocker was used when creating them in the genomorpher.
This milk has a rich, thick quality to it. It's origins, however, might be a bit dubious... Unless you trust mafia guys called Tony.
Scrambled together from a nailgun and outdated charge weapon technology this weapon is serviceable. Weak and short range, but quick.
Charged-shot energy/projectile semi automatic rifle made from whatever industrial equipment and broken charge weapon technology parts that could be scavenged.

A low-intelligent microcomputer that monitors the brain activity of its host. By periodically intercepting and altering signals in the brain it allows a person to find joy in whatever they are doing. While its not as dangerous and harmful as joywires it has the detrimental effect of making a person unable to gain true joy or fulfillment from something which would otherwise be beneficial to their mood. Due to such a detrimental side effect this implant is typically only used in questionable military organizations and black companies.
Uses mechanites to break down any object into its base materials, with near perfect efficiency.
A variety of tomatoes with a firm, meaty, rich, vibrant red colour. Its flavour is mild, juicy and balanced compared to other varieties.
Raw protein-rich lentil. Used in place of meat in recipes.

A small internal module designed to control the bodys reproduction functions.  Through the use of synthetic hormones and nanomachines the module is able to alter the users body achieving complete control of their organic functions relating to reproduction.

A payload of reptile genetic material. Can be used at the genomorpher to create a growth cell of a hybrid animal. This tier 2 genome can only be used as primary genome.  <color=#E5E54C>Gameplay effect:</color> All reptile hybrids have greatly increased minimum and maximum comfortable temperature. They also have melee and ranged venomous attacks.  <color=#E5E54C>Extraction:</color> Can only be extracted via any genome excavator from:

Directly injects reptile genes in an humanoid. This genetrainer gives the cold blood health state, making the subject more stealthy and resistant to high temperatures.  Genetrainers are implants that do not take the place of any given organ. Only one can be "installed" at a time. Using a second genetrainer will have no effect. Bear in mind that a genetrainer modifies the genes of the human subject, and only death will get rid of its effects.

Small and venomous, with a deadly fart, not quite what one was expecting for the perfect reptilian form. I mean, youd think youd get a tyrannosaurus rex or something but no, it seems that the humble iguana is here to stay. If anything, the shock of something so small moving so fast has got to be worth something.  A perfect reptile animal, paragon of all similar animals with no needless junk genetic data. Besides the various improvements to the baseline animals abilities, this paragon is oviparous and can manually rupture neck sacs containing venomous gas.
Fertilized reptile paragon egg. It can be eaten raw, but it's much, much better cooked. If all goes well, it should hatch into a reptile paragon.
Unfertilized reptile paragon egg. It can be eaten raw, but it's much, much better cooked.

A small durable core which contains a one-use super-dose of mechanites tuned to resurrect the dead. After the host dies, the core will sustain their mind and, when they choose, rebuild their body. The flesh will rapidly reform, replacing missing organs and healing wounds. The process is not perfect and may cause scarring or other health complications.
The RGD-5 High Explosive Grenade is essentially a capsule filled with explosives that will detonate on a timed fuse after being thrown.
A workbench for manufacturing Rimmu-Nation short barreled weapons such as handguns, PDWs and shotguns.
A workbench for manufacturing Rimmu-Nation heavy weapons such as GPMG, explosives and spacer weaponry.
A workbench for manufacturing Rimmu-Nation long barreled weapons such as automatic rifles, bolt action and marksman rifles.
A metallic wheel that is capable to withstand heavier chassis, it's also the frame of tyre.

Directly injects rodent genes in an humanoid. This genetrainer gives the gregarious health state, increasing all social capacities.  Genetrainers are implants that do not take the place of any given organ. Only one can be "installed" at a time. Using a second genetrainer will have no effect. Bear in mind that a genetrainer modifies the genes of the human subject, and only death will get rid of its effects.

Look, I know what youre thinking. Why is the rat the paragon of all rodents? And even if youre not thinking that, this is rhetorical anyway so there. What other rodent has caused civilization to collapse due to poorly held beliefs and lack of proper hygiene. As such, we give you the King Rat. Or Queen Rat, if you want a whole colony showing up.  A perfect rodent animal, paragon of all similar animals with no needless junk genetic data. Besides the various improvements to the baseline animals abilities, this paragon has a very fast gestation period and its attacks transmit the plague.

A payload of rodent genetic material. Can be used at the genomorpher to create a growth cell of a hybrid animal. This tier 1 genome can be used as either a primary or secondary genome.  <color=#E5E54C>Gameplay effect:</color> All rodent hybrids have a reduced body size, but greatly increased reproduction rates (if fertile).  <color=#E5E54C>Extraction:</color> Can be extracted via the genome extractor table or any genome excavator from:

The FAL (French: Fusil Automatique Lger, English: Light Automatic Rifle) is a battle rifle designed by Belgian small arms designers Dieudonn Saive and Ernest Vervier and manufactured by FN Herstal.  During the Cold War the FAL was adopted by many countries of the North Atlantic Treaty Organization (NATO), with the notable exception of the United States. It is one of the most widely used rifles in history, having been used by more than 90 countries. Because of its prevalence and widespread usage among the militaries of many NATO and first world countries during the Cold War it was given the title "The right arm of the Free World".

The RPD (Russian:    Ruchnoy Pulemyot Degtyaryova, English: Degtyaryov hand-held machine gun) is a 7.62mm light machine gun developed in the Soviet Union by Vasily Degtyaryov for the 7.6239mm M43 intermediate cartridge.

The RPG-7 (Russian: -7) is a portable, reusable, unguided, shoulder-launched, anti-tank rocket-propelled grenade launcher. Originally the RPG-7 (    Ruchnoy Protivotankoviy Granatomyot  Hand-held anti-tank grenade launcher) and its predecessor, the RPG-2, were designed by the Soviet Union; it is now manufactured by the Russian company Bazalt. The weapon has the GRAU index (Russian armed forces index) 6G3.     The ruggedness, simplicity, low cost, and effectiveness of the RPG-7 has made it the most widely used anti-armor weapon in the world. It is re-usable.

The RPK (Russian:   /, romanized: Ruchnoy Pulemyot Kalashnikova, English: "Kalashnikov's hand-held machine gun"), sometimes retroactively termed the RPK-47, is a Soviet 7.6239mm light machine gun that was developed by Mikhail Kalashnikov in the early 1960s, in parallel with the AKM assault rifle. It was created to standardize the small arms inventory of the Soviet Army, where it replaced the 7.6239mm RPD machine gun.

A complex grilled meat assembled with care from a wide selection of ingredients. This grill has been frozen, and as such it is still edible but much less filling. It won't provide the "well fed" buff.

A culinary work of art, characterized by refined, even elaborate preparation and presentation of an aesthetically balanced, albeit low quantity grilled meat. This grill has been frozen, and as such it is still edible but much less filling. It won't provide the "well fed" buff.

A masterpiece of the culinary arts, this grilled meat nourishes the body, mind, and soul. This grill has been frozen, and as such it is still edible but much less filling. It won't provide the "well fed" buff.
A simple grilled meat cooked from a few ingredients. This grill has been frozen, and as such it is still edible but much less filling. It won't provide the "well fed" buff.

The Smith & Wesson Model 36 (also known as the Chief's Special) is a revolver chambered for .38 Special. It is one of several models of J-frame revolvers. It was introduced in 1950, and is still in production in the classic blued Model 36 and the stainless steel Model 60.

The SA80 is a British family of 5.56x45mm NATO small arms, all of which are selective fire, gas-operated assault rifles. The L85 Rifle variant has been the standard issue service rifle of the British Armed Forces since 1987, replacing the L1A1 variant of the FN FAL. The first prototypes were created in 1976, with production of the A1 variant starting in 1985 and ending in 1994. The A2 variant came to be as the result of a significant upgrade in the early 2000s by Heckler and Koch and remains in service as of 2018. The A3 variant was first issued in 2018 with several new improvements.
A secure, lockable box for safely storing valuables against theft and/or damage from fire.  Note: protection from fire not yet implemented)

The Saiga-12 (/sa/) is a 12-gauge shotgun available in a wide range of configurations, patterned after the Kalashnikov series of rifles and named for the Saiga antelope. Like the Kalashnikov rifle variants, it is a rotating bolt, gas-operated gun that feeds from a box magazine. All Saiga-12 configurations are recognizable as Kalashnikov-pattern guns by the large lever-safety on the right side of the receiver, the optic mounting rail on the left side of the receiver and the large top-mounted dust cover held in place by the rear of the recoil spring assembly.

Small cherries that do not have much flesh beyond the seed within. Due to their bitter taste, sakuranbo are not traditionally eaten raw, but these fruits have been genetically modified to have a sweeter taste.
Rock salt, like common salt, enhances the flavor profile of other ingredients it is cooked with.
Salt is used into preservation of foods.
Meat that has been cured with salt.

A state-of-the-art holoprojector controlled by an AI. Its creativity allows for endless entertainment, customized to the user's tastes. The user will quickly gain skill points depending on the chosen sim.

The FN SCAR (Special Operations Forces Combat Assault Rifle) is a family of gas-operated short-stroke gas piston automatic rifles developed by Belgian manufacturer FN Herstal (FN) in 2004. It is constructed with modularity for the United States Special Operations Command (SOCOM) to satisfy the requirements of the SCAR competition. This family of rifles consists of two main types. The SCAR-L, for "light", is chambered in 5.5645mm NATO and the SCAR-H, for "heavy", is chambered in 7.6251mm NATO.

A dose of semi-coherent mechanites which reside in the nervous system and are designed to augment the host's senses.  This is the stable and safe form of whats commonly known as sensory mechanites.  Due to how mechanites work only one strain can exist harmoniously inside the hosts body.  However, it is possible to remove a mechanite strain with an expensive and difficult surgery.

A low-intelligent microcomputer that monitors the brain activity of its host.  Through constant conditioning, behaviour modifications and punishments it makes the host into a compliant and willing servant.  Due to the twisted design of the implant however it intentionally makes no attempts to appease the host in any way that matters.  As a result, the person undergoes horrific physical and mental suffering silently.  The Servitor Module is banned on all developed worlds, yet it can still be found in heavy use by slave traders and certain black companies.  The servitor module requires seven days to properly recondition its host.  During that time their consciousness will be temporarily lowered and they may undergo constant mental breaks with decreasing severity as they fight against the chip.  Due to the irreparable physiological damage it causes, the servitor module cannot be removed safely once its been installed.  Upon finishing reconditioning the host it provides the following benefits.  Provides +1000 mood. Removes the feeling of pain. Removes the need for recreation. Removes the need for rest. Prevents inspirations. Prevents mental breaks. Prevents starting social fights. Prevents forming opinions of others. Prevents bonding with animals.
