Efficiently stores up to 1,000Wd of energy.

A computer core capable of housing a superhumanlike AI who can pilot your ship, accurately fire its weapons, or guide it on interstellar journeys. Includes a mechanite breeding tank which allows the AI to manifest a formgel avatar.
Advanced spacecraft systems, relatively intact. Can be deconstructed to yield spacer components.
Nutrient-rich fermented hay and grains for your animals. The fermentation process preserves the silage preventing rot.
A simple bake quickly cooked from a few ingredients and flour.
A simple dessert quickly made from a few fruits and other ingredients.
A simple grilled meat cooked from a few ingredients. Very filling, grilled meats allow people to not feel hunger for a long time. Freezing them ruins this effect.
A simple soup slow cooked from a few ingredients.

A large metal bin for tossing heavy things in.  These skips are not covered; they are open to the weather.  Note: tossing large amounts of steel in willy-nilly means that it takes a while to find the steel you want later.  The mod author has abstracted that as a longer time for storing large stacks of items.  Pretend your pawns have to climb in and stack everything so the doggies can pick it up easily.

The korpion vz. 61 is a Czechoslovak 7.65 mm machine pistol developed in 1959 by Miroslav Ryb (19241970) and produced under the official designation Samopal vzor 61 ("submachine gun model 1961") by the esk zbrojovka arms factory in Uhersk Brod from 1961 to 1979.  Although it was developed for use with security forces and special forces, the weapon was also accepted into service with the Czechoslovak Army, as a personal sidearm for lower-ranking army staff, vehicle drivers, armoured vehicle personnel and special forces. Currently the weapon is in use with the armed forces of several countries as a sidearm.

The SKS is a Soviet semi-automatic carbine chambered for the 7.6239mm round, designed in 1943 by Sergei Gavrilovich Simonov. Its complete designation, SKS-45, is an initialism for Samozaryadny Karabin sistemy Simonova, 1945 (Russian:    , 1945; Self-loading Carbine of (the) Simonov system, 1945).    The SKS-45 was manufactured at Tula Arsenal from 1949 to 1958 and at Izhevsk Arsenal in just 1953 and 1954, resulting in a total Soviet production of about 2.7 million carbines.
A thickened, fatty substance made by churning milk into very thick cream, combining with smokeleaf oil and allowing it to set. Very unhealthy and hits quite a bit harder than a joint.
A sweet drink made from fruit and milk.   Food Effects: Moving and Blood Pumping.

Possibly one of the weirdest and cutest snakes to be ever created. They have several tiny legs which are used to push its body along, while also having an invitingly soft fur. Quite a lot of people never stop freaking out from something sliding up the backs of their legs only to get softly headbutted by a purring python.  A reptile hybrid with recessive feline genes. An unusually furry snake that enjoys nuzzling while also hunting for prey much weaker than itself. Incredibly intelligent and easy to train, they combine quick reflexes and an incredibly nasty bite and spitting attack.  <color=#E5E54C>Gameplay effect:</color> All reptile hybrids have good temperature tolerance ranges and venomous attacks.
Raw snow beet.

The AN/PEQ-1 also known as a Special Operations Forces Laser Acquisition Marker (SOFLAM or SOF-LAM) is a U.S. military laser designator designed for use by special operations forces, under more rugged field conditions.
An advanced telescope for doing amateur astronomy. It's a relaxing hobby for a certain kind of person. Includes its own reinforced window slot so it can be used under ship roofs.

A high-tech bed perfect for a sleepy baby. In the event of life support failure, a protective shell will close around the occupant, recycling oxygen and regulating temperature. It also functions as an escape pod if the ship is critically damaged.  It is not a cryptosleep casket and cannot keep its occupant alive during interstellar journeys.

The Spartan Marine is a Synthetic 2+1 capacity Semi Automatic 12 Gauge Shotgun, a military style Marine Semi Auto shotgun in traditional silver and Black. It is manufactured by Spartan Arms for the civilian market built with 2+1 capacity with  3 magnum chamber and uses mobil chokes.

The Franchi SPAS-12 is a combat shotgun manufactured by Italian firearms company Franchi from 1979 to 2000. The SPAS-12 is a dual-mode shotgun, adjustable for semi-automatic or pump-action operation. The SPAS-12 was sold to military and police users worldwide on the civilian market and has been featured in many movies, TV shows, and video games.

The spatha was a type of straight and long sword, measuring between 0.5 and 1 m (19.7 and 39.4 in), with a handle length between 18 and 20 cm (7.1 and 7.9 in), in use in the territory of the Roman Empire during the 1st to 6th centuries AD. Later swords, from the 7th to 10th centuries, like the Viking swords, are recognizable derivatives and sometimes subsumed under the term spatha.

A dose of semi-coherent mechanites which develop fibrous links in muscle tissue in order to augment the host's speed.  Due to how mechanites work only one strain can exist harmoniously inside the hosts body.  However, it is possible to remove a mechanite strain with an expensive and difficult surgery.

Spelt flour, ideal for use in baking. Spelt flour takes a very long time to go bad, if stored in a dry environment. It was produced by spelt that has been genetically engineered to gently break into flour with a mere touch.
A variety of aromatic and pungent spices, adds several sharp notes on the tongue and puts a bit of a pep in your step.

People really never understand what it is to have a bad hair day, and this feisty feline is gonna help teach them. As for those who dont want to be covered in hairballs formed from silk strands and adhesive mucus, thems the brakes, kid. Dont wanna get spat on, then be friends with them and get over your arachnophobia.  An insectoid hybrid with recessive feline genes. Both quick and decent offensive power, this one can handle themselves in both melee combat and a blinding ranged attack. A little difficult to train, but very clever and affectionate with flexible scales to resist cuts.  <color=#E5E54C>Gameplay effect:</color> All insectoid hybrids have good armor and no toxic sensitivity, but they are always sterile and can't reproduce, even if a fertility booster is used to create them.

Arachnophobia is no joke for many people, and the researcher that created this armoured arachnid had an inherent desire to share their fear with others. Granted they passed out, frothing at the mouth, when the creature emerged from the pod, but damn it its hard to argue with results in a riding companion that can not only keep up with the competition, but also disable them and eat them on the go as a tasty snack.  An equine hybrid with recessive insectoid genes. A rather slow and filthy hybrid of this category, but it works very well as a ride due to the multiple legs easing the burden of long distance travel inherent to caravaning. However, their main advantage is that they are also incredibly capable in combat, being armour plated and capable of both high damage and ranged stunning attacks by shooting globs of sticky threads.  <color=#E5E54C>Gameplay effect:</color> All equine hybrids are good for caravaning. A caravan with one of them needs a shorter resting period, only stopping to rest between 23:30 PM and 4 AM.

Neutroamine is rather difficult to manufacture due to the sterile environment needed in creating a synthetic precursor chemical. So some insane madman decided to create a living creature that can synthesise its own neutroamine. Granted its not a lot, but have enough of these disturbingly powerful and quick cobras and no one will ever try to rob you, or live long enough to get away.  A reptile hybrid with recessive insectoid genes. For an animal so small, it has an incredibly powerful bite and can spit venom. Sadly they cant be trained but will happily hunt smaller prey that happen to wander into their territory or fight back against any foolish predators. Can be milked once every several days for a vial of neutroamine, so they function well as part of a large drug farm.  <color=#E5E54C>Gameplay effect:</color> All reptile hybrids have good temperature tolerance ranges and venomous attacks.

Its small, its cute, its a ticking time bomb waiting for some idiot to think it looks delicious. Its not going to be a big explosion, but that doesnt matter much when its in your mouth.  A rodent hybrid with recessive boomalope genes. Small, weak but fast, this hybrid suits those looking for a fuel production method in a small package. Produces chemfuel much more efficiently compared to a boomalope but it needs to be milked every day.  <color=#E5E54C>Gameplay effect:</color> All rodent hybrids have fast gestation, as long as a fertility unblocker was used when creating them in the genomorpher.

Compressed medicine that slows the growth of the specimen, increasing both stability and safety. Effectively increases growth time by 50% in exchange for a vastly increased chance of obtaining the intended result.

Compressed medicine that allows hybrids to develop functional sexual organs. Effectively allows hybrids to reproduce with the exact same species.  This booster can't be crafted, only scavenged.  Note: Insectoid hybrids are always incapable of reproducing.
a heat engine that performs mechanical work using steam as its working fluid, it's common used by early industrial vehicles such as steam tractor and truck.

A vacuum-adapted variant of the familiar spelopede, the stellapede's anaerobic metabolism allows it to survive in space indefinitely. It appears to subsist primarily on minerals, but will eagerly hunt any organic prey it senses.

Manufactured by an American firearm company based in Georgetown, Texas. The STI 2011 are modular M1911-style semi-automatic pistols designed for competition, duty and self-defense. All firearms are designed, engineered, and handcrafted in Texas with 100% American materials and parts.   The STI 2011 Combat Master has been beautifully tuned from the original version at Taran Tactical Innovations. This particular version was used by a legendary assassin known as "Baba Yaga".
Cooking technique in which ingredients are fried in a small amount of very hot oil.   Food Effects: Manipulation and Blood Filtration.

The STK 100 is a striker fired pistol developed by Rock Island Armoury as a competitor and improvement from the Glock series. It boasts a lighter frame and less cost of resources to manufacture while maintaining the same reliability and durability of it's predecessor.

The Stoeger Coach Gun is a double-barreled shotgun. It is marketed and distributed by Stoeger Industries in Accokeek, Maryland. It is manufactured by E.R. Amantino (Boito) in Veranpolis, Brazil.  The Coach Gun is a side-by-side shotgun. While suitable for bird hunting, clay target shooting, or home defense, it is primarily designed for cowboy action shooting. As the name implies, it is a coach gun style shotgun, similar to those used to defend stagecoaches in the American Old West.

A dose of semi-coherent mechanites which develop fibrous links in muscle tissue in order to augment the host's strength.  This is the stable and safe form of whats commonly known as fibrous mechanites.  Due to how mechanites work only one strain can exist harmoniously inside the hosts body.  However, it is possible to remove a mechanite strain with an expensive and difficult surgery.
Harvested canes from the sugar-cane plant.

This simple brain implant was designed to subdue rebellious slaves without harming them. By itself its completely benign, however, when hit by an electromagnetic pulse it will knock the host unconscious.

An axe (sometimes ax in American English; see spelling differences) is an implement that has been used for millennia to shape, split and cut wood, to harvest timber, as a weapon, and as a ceremonial or heraldic symbol. The axe has many forms and specialised uses but generally consists of an axe head with a handle, or helve.  This variant of axe is the Gerber Bear Grylls Survival Axe.

An emergency survival belt used by starship crews. It remains dormant so long as air pressure is maintained. Once exposed to vacuum, the belt releases a semi-liquid membrane over the user's body and begins generating breathable air. For the next three hours, the user can survive exposure to vacuum, although their movements are slowed. The belt is single-use.

One of mankind's oldest manufactured objects. The knife has taken many forms, but the concept has always remained the same: A handle for holding and a sharp edge for cutting.  This survival knife is of the First Blood variant.

One of mankind's oldest manufactured objects. The knife has taken many forms, but the concept has always remained the same: A handle for holding and a sharp edge for cutting.  This survival knife is of the Gerber Bear Grylls variant.

The SV-98 (Snaiperskaya Vintovka Model 1998) is a Russian bolt-action sniper rifle designed by Vladimir Stronskiy. In 2003 special operations troops were armed with the 7.62 mm 6S11 sniper system comprising the SV-98 sniper rifle (index 6V10) and 7N14 sniper enhanced penetration round.    The rifle has been used in combat during operations in Chechnya.
A sweet roll covered in sugary icing.
Makes sweet treats.

A sword is an edged, bladed weapon intended for manual cutting or thrusting. Its blade, longer than a knife or dagger, is attached to a hilt and can be straight or curved. A thrusting sword tends to have a straighter blade with a pointed tip. A slashing sword is more likely to be curved and to have a sharpened cutting edge on one or both sides of the blade. Many swords are designed for both thrusting and slashing.  This variant is the "Zombie Killer" sword made in the modern era, initially designed to be a gimmick for fans of the horror genre.

A low-intelligent microcomputer that monitors the brain activity of its host. After assessing the host, it works with them to take over the brain functionality the hosts brain is incapable of. In doing so its able restore the hosts brain functionality back to what can be considered normal. Due to how the unit functions it strictly regulates a hosts consciousness allowing it to neither rise nor fall regardless of outside factors.  The implant itself is widely used in less developed worlds who have trouble curing brain injuries.  It is also sometimes used by military organizations to keep soldiers up and fighting even if they develop head injuries during the line of duty.

An advanced artificial skin gland built by an archotech. The gland releases chemicals and nanomachines that remodels the users skin, making it flawless and tougher than plasteel. Its internal workings are a mystery to all human minds.
Meat and Cheese in a Corn shell.   Food Effects: Metabolism and Manipulation.
A chewy sweet candy made from sugar and fruit juices.   Food Effects: Moving.

A tant (, "short sword") is one of the traditionally made Japanese swords (nihonto) that were worn by the samurai class of feudal Japan. The tant dates to the Heian period, when it was mainly used as a weapon but evolved in design over the years to become more ornate. Tant were used in traditional martial arts (tantojutsu). The term has seen a resurgence in the West since the 1980s as a point style of modern tactical knives, designed for piercing or stabbing.  This tanto knife is of the Cold Steel variant.

The IWI Tavor is an Israeli bullpup assault rifle chambered in 5.56x45mm NATO caliber with a selective fire system, selecting between semi-automatic mode and full automatic fire mode.  The Tavor is designed and produced by Israel Weapon Industries (IWI). It is produced in two main variants: the TAR-21 and the CTAR-21.
Tea leaves for brewing.

This is a techprint for the research project 'Advanced Bionics'.  The physical form of techprints can range from scraps of paper with diagrams, all the way to advanced self-contained teaching machines. Regardless of form, they play the same role. They give your researchers the confidence that an idea is possible, and a rough idea of the designs used in more established societies.  Your researchers need the foundational knowledge offered by techprints to know where to start on a given technology. Only after enough techprints have been applied can your researchers work out the fine details of how to make use of the technology in your particular situation.  Applying techprints to a satisfied project fulfills half the remaining research progress. In addition, researchers always gain a boost to their intellectual skills when applying techprints, even on already-completed technologies. Absolutely and completely worthless, but when properly processed alongside an actual genome it can be trimmed down to an identical copy.
Capsules containing growth hormones that help speed up the hybrids growth process, halving the time it takes to complete.
A garment which barely covers the wearer, just enough to cover the important bits. Does not come with a Multi-Pass.

An implant designed to help regulate the bodies temperature allowing a person to endure harsher cold and heat without ill effects.  The implant integrates seamlessly with the body's natural systems, employing a combination of microthermal regulators and advanced bio-coolants. The implant constantly monitors the body's core temperature through a network of nanosensors embedded in the skin and circulatory system. When exposed to high temperatures, the system activates micro-cooling channels that dissipate heat by circulating a special coolant through the body. Conversely, in cold environments, the implant triggers a micro-heating mechanism, increasing blood flow and gently warming tissues to maintain a stable internal temperature.
Used to control electric and gas boilers. More than one can be placed. Connects via standard plumbing.
Coarse, strong wool. Provides heat and cold protection, as well as decent defense.
Brittle, strange smelling wool. Not the best wool to craft apparel with, though it's better than nothing. Provides nice heat insulation.

The Thompson submachine gun is an American submachine gun, invented by John T. Thompson in 1918, that became infamous during the Prohibition era, becoming a signature weapon of various crime syndicates in the United States. It was a common sight in the media of the time, being used by both law enforcement officers and criminals.   The Thompson submachine gun was also known informally as the "Tommy Gun", "Annihilator", "Chicago Typewriter", "Chicago Piano", "Chicago Style", "Chicago Organ Grinder", "Trench Broom", "Trench Sweeper", "The Chopper", and simply "The Thompson".

Now heres a creature you absolutely want to keep properly fed, and youre going to need entire fields to support a single one. The ridiculous amount of chemfuel they produce means that the ceasing of their life functions is more accurately described as thermonuclear. So if they are going to blow up, send them as a surprise gift to friends and family who keep trying to kill you.  A colossal hybrid with recessive boomalope genes. The addition of chemfuel production has vastly increased the amount of food they need to survive, but theyre also smart enough to not need a pen. Consider keeping them far away from your growing fields if the local biome can grow vegetation fast enough to support one.  <color=#E5E54C>Gameplay effect:</color> All colossal hybrids have very slow attacks, but hit very hard, and possess natural armor.

If you thought Thrumbos were tough and hit like a tank, may I present to you the answer to all your prayers. If you can feed the thing, this absolute unit would work extremely well as an assault force against any force foolish enough to threaten its feedstock. Plus you get to ride it on long journeys, possibly clearing entire forests on the way.  A colossal hybrid with recessive ursine genes. While proportionately it has a lower metabolism, its 50% increase in size still leaves it with a higher hunger rate than a thrumbo. They are however easier to train, hit much harder and can take even more punishment.  <color=#E5E54C>Gameplay effect:</color> All colossal hybrids have very slow attacks, but hit very hard, and possess natural armor.

The other half of the super predator duo, along with the Thrumwolf, exchanging some ferocity and durability in exchange for going for the trachea and spitting suffocating hairballs. That might not sound that dangerous but imagine having a fistful of hair pulled from a shower drain smothering your mouth, and youll realise thats still not disgusting enough. But for those that it appreciates, it will often pin them down and snuggle them given the chance.  A colossal hybrid with recessive feline genes. A large predator with an insane appetite with a focus on ferocious attacks that restrict their preys breathing. Extremely agile with a soft spot for those it loves, best suited for biomes that support enough wildlife to sate its hunger.  <color=#E5E54C>Gameplay effect:</color> All colossal hybrids have very slow attacks, but hit very hard, and possess natural armor.

This is probably the closest chickens will be able to get to recovering their past glory as super predators. Theyll often hunt any other animal for their next meal, multiple times a day, and you havent yet lived until youve ridden one on a long journey. If they could be further bred to cross mountains and oceans, theyd be almost perfect.  A colossal hybrid with recessive avian genes. The combination of genes has turned this somewhat peaceful herbivore/dendrovore into a full carnivore, which makes it easier to support their large appetite. As an intelligent predator, it can move incredibly quickly for its size and its attacks are incredibly fierce. It also lays massive eggs that can feed entire families.  <color=#E5E54C>Gameplay effect:</color> All colossal hybrids have very slow attacks, but hit very hard, and possess natural armor.
Fertilized Thrumbochicken egg. If all goes well, it should hatch into one of these abominations. It can be eaten raw, but it's much better cooked.
Unfertilized Thrumbochicken egg. It can be eaten raw, but it's much, much better cooked.

About as close as anyone has ever gotten in making a recreation of dragons from folklore. Capable of surviving in extreme cold or heat, the only thing really missing is a pair of wings and an innate desire to hoard piles of gold for a nest. That and the fact that it isnt carnivorous, instead having an appetite for vegetables and wood fibres.  A colossal hybrid with recessive reptile genes. With a mouth dripping with venom and tough, flexible scales covering the body, this hybrid makes for a nasty and incredibly durable combat hybrid. If that wasnt enough, it can also breath out a fog of noxious fumes and move deceptively quickly.  <color=#E5E54C>Gameplay effect:</color> All colossal hybrids have very slow attacks, but hit very hard, and possess natural armor. All reptile hybrids have good temperature tolerance ranges and venomous attacks.

Look, we know what you want, a thrumbo that wont eat your crops before theyve harvested, thereby wasting entire seasons of growth for your most valuable plants. And were here to tell you it doesnt exist. But weve gotten close in that this one will typically harvest your plants before it eats them for worse nutritional gain. Unless its trees, in which case we got nothing.  A colossal hybrid with recessive humanoid genes. Considerably easier to train and maintain, this particular hybrid will help around the colony by cutting and harvesting designated plants. Unusually lean for how much it eats, it wont provide much in butchering.  <color=#E5E54C>Gameplay effect:</color> Humanoid hybrids will periodically engage other colonists in conversation, talking about a variety of topics. This increases the social recreation needs of those they interact with by 10% (subject to diminishing returns like all joy types). If using Ideology, humanoid hybrids are subject to precepts. All colossal hybrids have very slow attacks, but hit very hard, and possess natural armor. Thrumbomen will obey orders to cut and harvest plants around the colony.

Practically an overgrown and intelligent pest capable of tunnelling underground, so not even a nuke could clear an infestation. And it truly would be an infestation, as it has a gestation period measured in days rather than weeks, with a single breeding pair capable of wiping out an entire agricultural planet.  A colossal hybrid with recessive rodent genes. Incredibly durable and fast breeding, this surprisingly small hybrid can work as a durable screening force. One of the weakest colossal hybrids in terms of attack power but very few can outlast its incredibly robust physique.  <color=#E5E54C>Gameplay effect:</color> All colossal hybrids have very slow attacks, but hit very hard, and possess natural armor. Burrow underground: Thrumborats can burrow underground to make them almost immune to damage for a short while.

A leftover bioweapon from a now extinct civilisation designed to completely eradicate biomes with dense vegetation. Records indicate that the local indigineous tribes were very resistant to corporate takeover and the megacorp in charge wanted to reduce profit losses. Eventually the planet starved as they were unable to stop these creatures from feasting on farmlands and food reserves.  A colossal hybrid with recessive insectoid genes. A slow moving tank with limited regenerative capabilities, they are almost unkillable if it werent for their crippling hunger. As durable as a capital ship, any colony that could possibly support the diet of even a single one would be considered impervious to raids.  <color=#E5E54C>Gameplay effect:</color> All colossal hybrids have very slow attacks, but hit very hard, and possess natural armor. They are always sterile and can't reproduce, even if a fertility booster is used to create them.

One of the largest creatures in existence, dwarfing even the thrumbo and the mighty Gallatross. Capable of transporting a massive amount of material, producing a luxurious and excellent wool as well as thick, nutritious milk, they are almost the perfect farm animal. That is as long as you dont look at your feed costs and die of a heart attack, but the scientists that designed this hybrid never had to worry about such things. Food is something for the proles to worry about.  A colossal hybrid with recessive muffalo genes. Completely herbivorous and with an appetite large enough to cause even large colonies to starve within a single season. This hybrid can prove worth the food costs as it produces thick, delicious milk every couple of days as well as luxurious wool every couple of seasons. Slightly more dimwitted than its progenitor and will attempt to wander off in search of food if not kept penned up.  <color=#E5E54C>Gameplay effect:</color> All colossal hybrids have very slow attacks, but hit very hard, and possess natural armor.
Thrumffalo Gouda is considered a refined delicacy. It takes a very long time to ripen, but once it is ready it is one of the most nourishing cheeses available on the Rim.
Milk from a thrumffalo. Very nutritive. Also with a sky-high cholesterol content, but in the Rim nobody judges you.

A very nice combination of two highly adaptive baseline creatures which arguably results in the best riding companion man could ask for. While this isnt apparent in their speed, it definitely is so once a rider experiences the thundering beats of this horsey positively barreling through entire forests and marshland in order to earn its next sugar cube the size of a fist.  A colossal hybrid with recessive equine genes. While they have a lower muscle-to-fat ratio compared to their progenitor, the overall placement and shape of the horn vastly reduces their combat efficiency. Instead, they more than make up for this shortfall with an incredible endurance even compared to paragons. An excellent riding companion that is easier to train and can even carry an acceptable amount of luggage, the majority of which contains feed.  <color=#E5E54C>Gameplay effect:</color> All equine hybrids are good for caravaning. A caravan with one of them needs a shorter resting period, only stopping to rest between 23:30 PM and 4 AM. Always starts as draftable, even if not using a controller booster to create it. Charge ability: when drafted, the player can use the charge ability to make the hybrid jump towards a target and cause massive damage with its horn to a single random body part. The ability can be triggered every 2 hours.

Theres a saying about the scientific community, namely your scientists were so preoccupied with whether they could, they didnt stop to think if they should. This is entirely relevant to this creature, a super predator with practically no equal, a single one of these is enough to require an entire rainforest to support their daily sustenance. If that wasnt bad enough, they were made along with the Thrumbocat as part of a duo.  A colossal hybrid with recessive canine genes. A large predator with an insane appetite with the necessary ferocity to support itself, very few colonies can support the diet of such a hybrid. Incredibly robust, fast and a terrifying ferocity, they will hunt multiple times a day and often go after prey much bigger than themselves.  <color=#E5E54C>Gameplay effect:</color> All colossal hybrids have very slow attacks, but hit very hard, and possess natural armor.

A workplace accident waiting to happen, the Tissue Grinder takes the corpses of animals and carefully rips and tears them to pieces in order to extract useful genetic data in the form of Genoframes. The hardware is also capable of combining two identical frames into a superior form by comparing and improving upon latent and inferior genetic material.  Workspeed is influenced by someone who actually knows what theyre looking for in order to skip some of the more routine tasks, and possibly shouldnt be placed into the hands of someone with no concept of ethics, morality or conscience.  <color=#E5E54C>Gameplay notes:</color> Bear in mind that the cost in corpses effectively doubles for each quality level, making a legendary genoframe prohibitive. The main usefulness of these recipes is to convert two genoframes of a given quality to a higher one, but your main source of genoframes shouldn't be hand crafting them. Go out there and explore abandoned labs!
Raw tobacco. Not recommended for eating, but makes for a nice smoke
Raw protein-rich Tofu. Made from Beans. Nice to eat, even when raw.

A tomahawk is a type of single-handed axe native to the many Indigenous peoples and nations of North America, traditionally resembling a hatchet with a straight shaft. The term came into the English language in the 17th century as an adaptation of the Powhatan (Virginian Algonquian) word. Tomahawks were general-purpose tools used by Native Americans and later the European colonials with whom they traded, and often employed as a hand-to-hand weapon.  This variant is the Gerber Tomahawk.

A tomahawk is a type of single-handed axe native to the many Indigenous peoples and nations of North America, traditionally resembling a hatchet with a straight shaft. The term came into the English language in the 17th century as an adaptation of the Powhatan (Virginian Algonquian) word. Tomahawks were general-purpose tools used by Native Americans and later the European colonials with whom they traded, and often employed as a hand-to-hand weapon.  This variant is the USMC Tomahawk.
An engine powered by gas expansion driving turbine blades, but fuel consumption is quite high. widely used in pre-spacer jets and military vehicles.
an airbreathing jet engine which is typically used in aircraft, consists of a gas turbine with a propelling nozzle.

A cheeky little shit that likes to go around and play with switches, to satisfy their curiosity much like how an ignorant child would. Perhaps a little too smart for their own good. Their behaviour is similar to failed service animals that learn how to operate household items without restraint.  An avian hybrid with recessive humanoid genes. Surprisingly hardy, quick and very intelligent, these creatures make for a particularly filthy and hungry egg-layer. Their little wings are quite dextrous and can be used to flick switches.  <color=#E5E54C>Gameplay effect:</color> Humanoid hybrids will periodically engage other colonists in conversation, talking about a variety of topics. This increases the social recreation needs of those they interact with by 10% (subject to diminishing returns like all joy types). If using Ideology, humanoid hybrids are subject to precepts. Turkeymen periodically flick switches around the colony (any building that can be toggled on / off by a colonist).
Fertilized turkeyman egg. If all goes well, it should hatch into one of these abominations. It can be eaten raw, but it's much better cooked.
Unfertilized turkeyman egg. It can be eaten raw, but it's much, much better cooked.

The Type 56 is a Chinese 7.6239mm assault rifle. It is a variant of the Soviet-designed AK-47 and AKM assault rifles. Production started in 1956 at State Factory 66 but was eventually handed over to Norinco, who continues to manufacture the rifle primarily for export.  During the Cold War period, the Type 56 was exported to many countries and guerrilla forces throughout the world. Many of these rifles found their way to battlefields in Africa, Southeast Asia, and the Middle East and were used alongside other Kalashnikov pattern weapons from both the Soviet Union as well the Warsaw Pact nations of Eastern Europe.

The Type 81 (Chinese: 81; literally; "Type 81 Automatic Rifle") is a Chinese-designed second-generation, selective-fire, gas-operated 7.6239mm rifle (based on Kalashnikov and SKS actions) adopted by the Chinese People's Liberation Army (PLA) and has been in service since the mid-1980s.  It's a small arms family that consist of the Type 81, the Type 81-1 and the Type 81 LMG.

The Type CQ is an unlicensed Chinese variant of the M16 rifle manufactured by Norinco. According to the Norinco website, the rifle is officially known as CQ 5.56.  It can be distinguished from other AR-15 and M-16 pattern rifles by its long, revolver-like pistol grip, somewhat rounded handguards, and the unique shape of its stock.
An advanced wheel consisting of an air-filled outer wheel and a metal rim.

The Heckler and Koch UMP (Universale Maschinenpistole, German for "Universal Submachine Gun") is a submachine gun developed and manufactured by Heckler and Koch. The UMP has been adopted by various agencies such as the U.S. Customs and Border Protection. Heckler and Koch developed the UMP as a lighter and cheaper successor to the MP5, though both remain in production.
An uncooked fine soup. This needs to be cooked in an electric pot to be edible.
An uncooked gourmet soup. This needs to be cooked in an electric pot to be edible.
An uncooked lavish soup. This needs to be cooked in an electric pot to be edible.
An uncooked simple soup. This needs to be cooked in an electric pot to be edible.
